Product name: Antique OOAK folk art child's scooter, original paint, handmade, circa early 1900s
Description:
What a wonderful example of a one-of-a-kind toy handmade for a special young man in the early 1900's. I know that because it was purchased from the estate of the original owner & comes with a photograph of him out for a ride in his Sunday finest. The charming little three wheeled scooter is hand made from pine & still retains much of the original green paint.
The condition is remarkably good given that it is 90 years old. The collar on the front steering column is cracked and been repaired over the years, as evidenced by the presence of square nails & signs of old glue. We have chosen to leave the old repair, as is, as a reminder that this was a well loved toy. 
Built for a toddler, the scooter measures 17" long x 16.5" high at the handle. The rear wheelbase is 9" wide. The frame with the picture of the original owner is 13" x 10.5", 
This is a fun example of early American folk art that is looking for a new home.
Shipping to the US is 30.

Product name: Vintage Horse and Wagon Coin Operated Kiddie Ride
Description:
Please be sure to read shipping information at the end of this description.
This is an early coin operated kiddie ride. It is a horse with a wagon behind it. I sort of think originally it was a fire hose wagon. It was most likely made by Bally and has a wooden base.
It utilizes an early timer set-up in the original coin box. It works well and is working off the coin mechanism. It takes one quarter for a ride. There is a set of new locking swivel casters mounted underneath the base for easy movement.
The base has some wear to the wood and has been repainted. There are some chips, rubs and wear to the body throughout. It measures approximately 67" long, 28 1/2" wide and 44 1/2" tall.

Description:
Mulitifunctional cable bag, to organise and protect your earbuds and other items.
_
I create those drawings from a need to recenter. Drawing has this power to put the soul at ease and I love to share some of the outcomes with you. 
As the idealistic artist I am, I feel an urge to share the silence that we all need to put ourselves at rest in this extremely loud world we live in. Writing can help with that and so the drawingnotebook receipe was born. It's also an ode to all the writers out there: you are so valuable and life-changing!
I remember reading Paulo Coelho's The Alchemist and Henry and June (Anaïs Nin) for the first time and it totally changed my perspective on how we live our lives. Reading both books and a bunch of blogs allows me to connect with people in other worlds and other times to explore so many experiences together.
To see more of my work please visit www.joriekerottier.nl

Product name: Antique Long Paste Georgian Earrings
Description:
These spectacular long silver / gold earrings are steeped in history.
These look spectacular when worn, the Old Cut Paste stones glisten and sparkle continuously.
When you look at these lovely Georgian earrings, they take you on a journey
over 200 years old, probably from an old lavaliere originally and they have been broken
up to make earrings, the 18ct yellow gold wires have been added over the years.
Paste is a heavy, very transparent flint glass that stimulates the fire and brilliance of gemstones
because it has relatively high indices of refraction and strong dispersion
The Romans in particular were very skilful in the production of coloured - glass pastes
Perfect for a wedding
Set with a closed backed silver gallery and 18ct gold wires
Excellent condition all round.
They weigh 16.8 grams
We can provide a written Valuation on completion of sale.
The earrings measures 58mm in  length
The bottom section measures 25mm across

Product name: 18th Century Portuguese Iberian Lazo Earrings with Foiled Amethyst
Description:
Dramatic and romantic Iberian earrings, circa 1790-1810.  Each earring is separated into four sections, each designed to move separately, so that the deep purple amethysts and all the diamonds will  twinkle and glisten as they catch the light.  These earrings were so exquisitely made.  
A little background:  "Iberian" is the term used for 18th Century (Georgian era)  jewelry from Spain or Portugal.  When Spain and Portugal had colonized South America, incredible gems from Brazil and emeralds from the famous Muzo mines in Columbia found their way into earrings, rings, etc.  which were designed with such expert craftsmanship that they often remain in excellent, wearable condition even today, despite their age.  "Lazo" refers to the bow motif from the Spanish for "bow".  
These are chock full of diamonds, a mixture of rose cuts and old mine cuts, along with foiled amethysts in gold, closed back settings.  The diamonds are set in silver.  They are quite substantial and heavy, but not uncomfortably so.  
The earrings have posts, which were added in modern times.  They are a little over 2 inches in length.  The larger old mine cuts may be replacements, but if so, they were replaced in antiquity.  There are early Portuguese marks to the back.

Angela Caputi established the company "Giuggiù" in 1975 in Florence. Angela Caputi is today one of the most recognized names in the field of high fashion costume jewelry carrying the "Made in Italy" label.
Her Production and designs are precise and very distinctive. Angela adores to mix various materials, creating always particular combinations of colours and textures. The outcome is coloured, original jewelery, made in plastic and synthetic materials, something unique which is her personal trademark.

Product name: Antique Ring - 22k Gold French Napoleon III Empire Natural Pearl Victorian Ring, Antique Jewelry Victorian Jewelry Statement size 7
Description:
Antique Pearl Ring | Victorian Ring | French Empire Ring
A rare and incredible 19th century French antique ring, of solid 22K gold casted in the form of double openwork laurel wreaths encircling deftly suspended natural pearls, and connecting to a ring shank with shoulders chased in the 'branche de laurier' pattern. Weighing an unusual 5.9 grams, this is a substantial and gorgeous piece-- the incredible richness of the 22k gold pairs well with the luminous translucency of the sea-harvested natural pearls (i.e. not farm cultivated from an artificial nucleus).
Though crafted between 1860-80 during the "Second French Empire" period, this ring is stylistically rooted in the 1810s neoclassicism of Napoleon Bonaparte's First French Empire. This "Empire Style", as it is commonly called today, provided a kind of visual & aesthetic vocabulary for Napoleon's consolidation of power. Archeological motifs from ancient Rome, such as the gold laurel wreaths seen on this ring, were adapted to evoke the elegance and stoic virtues of Republican Rome, while finesse of craftsmanship and adoption of bold, ostentatious colors (such as gold, red, and black) lent Empire style decorative arts a sense of grandeur and authority. Indeed, this ring is all at once reserved, elegant, and glamorously chic. Art and designs from the First French Empire proved to be so enduring that European monarchies adapted its look throughout the 19th century, even after the fall of Napoleon I. The Empire style experienced a particularly strong revival in France during the monarchical restorations of Louis Philippe I and Louis-Napoléon Bonaparte (later Emperor Napoléon III).
-~- Details -~-

Description:
An old French Loto game in a beautifully labelled wooden box with a wonderful french Image and Graphics on the lid. 
Loto (or Lotto) is a popular family board game in France and is basically Bingo. This set is complete with cards and 66 wooden "pions" or counters ( there would have been 90 originally) It is still in its original wooden box. I estimate this set dates to the 1930s.
The previous owner has written their name in beautiful handwriting on the inside lid of the box. People don't write like that anymore!
Would be a great nostalgic display decoration.
It is in well worn vintage condition, this game has clearly been used and enjoyed for many years. The box is a little worn and  the catch is broken although the lid closes perfectly.  The cards are all in good condition but some of them are a little faded.
The box simply looks wonderful on a book table. Great for storing other things in also. I have included some other French vintage language cards which came in the box. Great for learning French Words with pictures!

Description:
Custom Order your own ANTIQUE VANITY and mirror to be sourced, refinished and painted in any color. We only offer shabby chic furniture that will exude romance and old-world charm! 
YES! WE SHIP FURNITURE NATIONWIDE. 14 YEARS.
How it works: Add this order to your cart and let us know which style you love from the examples shown above. We'll locate your perfect antique vanity and send pre-work photos for your review. Once you approve the vanity, we will restore, enhance and refinish it in our fabulous shabby chic style. The custom order process takes roughly 10 weeks. We keep you up-to-date on the vanity's progress every step of the way.  500 down to get started, another 500 when the piece you love is found, balance due when vanity is finished, approved and ready to ship. At Check Out please mark payment as OTHER. This allows you to complete without paying in full. An invoice for the down will follow later. PayPal or credit card accepted.
Vanities are not in stock. We do not build them. They are from the 1920's era and are very well constructed from strong, old growth wood and with century-long durability unlike today's new furnishings. We restore to last another 100 years.
Our refinishing is always hand painted by brush, using only USA made water-based, no VOC, lead-free paints. We take our time and properly apply multiple coats of paint with a smooth silky feel, {chic} oh yes! We can add a touch, or a lot, of {shabby} with our unique weathered age distressed finesse. Named stock colors are our own custom blends (see color choices in the dropdown). We will also paint in your custom 1 color for an additional 50. Please inquire if you want metallic or multiple tone paint.
Mirrors typically will have age spots or ghosting but clear enough to apply makeup. The wood inside the drawers will have signs of use but get rejuvenated for a rich look. All drawers will open and close properly. Vanities have antique metal pulls and knobs with old patinas. The old wheels shown are not included, however, new hard wood replica wheels are available to buy. 
Most Economical Shipping: To your nearest Greyhound PackageXpress office for pick up. Insurance and extreme quality packing are included. Picking up from GPX is easy. Many GPX stations offer station-to-home delivery for a little more money if needed. Mirror will ship by FedEx. For additional  FedEx Ground shipping the base may be possible. Please contact us for rates to Hawaii, Alaska and Canada. No shipping charge if picking up at our shop in Oklahoma City.
WE ARE RED BARN ESTATES: We specialize in furniture for Paris Apartment, Shabby Chic Cottage, Beach House and Vacation homes. Our antique and vintage furniture is carefully restored. Most pieces have carved wood backsplashes we design. The old wood will have dents, nicks and dings here and there that add to the weathered, worn and distressed charm of the piece.

Product name: Black Forest Cuckoo Clock Vintage Deer Hunter Hunting Rifles Ammunition Bag Horn Animals Rabbit Pheasant Musical Carousel Dancers Thorens
Description:
An amazing vintage hand carved Black Forest cuckoo clock.  Clock has The deer head for the finial with the carved rifles to complete the crown.  Animated musical carousel dancers. Hand carved Rabbit and Pheasant along the sides.  The carved horn encircles the face of the clock.  Below you will see the ammunition bag.
 Cuckoo comes out on the hour, as well as the half hour.  The dancers come out on the hour, as well as the half hour. 
Particulars: This is a one day, three weight clock, which means it should run for 30 hours, but most people call them one day movements, as to remember to pull the chains up each day, in order to keep it running.  Back is stamped Made in Germany.  The side has a sticker reading Thorens Movement Frohliche Wanderer Holzhackerbub'n Made in Switzerland.  Thorens is the manufacturer of the musical movement for the dancers.  Inside is marked Hones Titiser-Neustadt West Germany on the clock works.
Measurements: Clock measures 23" from the top of the antlers to the bottom of the pendulum.
Also, all my clocks have been cleaned and  are in running order. If you are not familiar with setting up a clock you may want to find someone local who deals or works with antique clocks, as they have to be level and properly set up in order to run correctly.

Product name: Vintage French School Map Rossignol - Paris school geography map, Vintage map Paris, France, 50s, Wall decoration Old School Map - Map Paris
Description:
Vintage Rossignol school map representing Paris and its region. The map is printed on both sides.
These Rossignol maps were in every french school in the 50s and 60s. All french pupils studied geography with them! Today, they are subjects of nostalgia and so many memories!
We find them also very poetic. Looking at them makes one want to travel, or moved to recognize familiar places!
The historical perspective is also fascinating : so many geopolitical changes occurred in the world between the 50s and today. The challenge is to find all of them and use them to date these maps!
This vintage school map is 90 cm long and 75 cm wide (35.4 x 29.5 inches).
This map presents traces of use : some humidity brown marks and two small tears on two edges (see pictures).

Product name: Pink .. LOVE .. UNused US Vintage Postage Stamps  .. post 5 letters
Description:
Use these nostalgic vintage postage stamps to mail your cards or those invitations for a party.
OR
Use these unused unmarked stamps for your very special aceo, collage, jewelry or other creative creation.
S T O R Y
The first Love stamp, issued in 1973, proved so popular that a second stamp was issued in 1982 and then again in 1984 and 1985. Although the Love stamp was usually issued in time for use on Valentine's Day mail, it was intended to enhance cards and letters on many other special occasions throughout the year such as weddings, birthdays, and anniversaries. 
THIS LOT: all fine MINT UNused United States postage valid for current use as postage.
5 LOVE Pink Rose 1988 issue 25 cent stamps
5 Pink Flowers 1981 issue 18 cent stamps (4 unique designs)
5 Public reads 1943 issue 4cent stamps 
5 Lafayette 1957 issue 3cent stampms
Enough to post 5 - 1oz letters at .50 each. 
NOTE: one or more of the stamps used in your custom design are part of a setenant set of stamps. These stamps were issued and are sold, collected and traded as sets. You will receive an equal number of each stamp in the set.
Enjoy!
Postage Tip:  If you need more than the standard 49cents for your mailing you can use vintage postage alongside of current USPS stamps.  So you could use a current USPS stamp (you can see what they have to offer at the USPS website) and then add ??cents worth of vintage postage to complete the arrangement.  This can be a cost and space effective way to add that vintage touch.  Something old and something new!

Product name: BATHROOM VANITY Double or Single Sink We Custom Convert from Antique Furniture For You - Renovation - Nationwide Shipping
Description:
Vanity cabinet in 50" to 62" wide range. In converting, we preserve the "look" of the original antique piece while reinforcing the frame and making alterations making it more bath vanity friendly. Drawers may be converted to faux or into cabinet doors that still look like drawers. 
This gorgeous black bath cabinet was custom ordered by another Etsy buyer like yourself. It serves as an example for this custom order listing.
13 years furniture shipping nationwide and Canada.
Order now and we'll immediately start hunting down the perfect antique piece to turn into a gorgeous, unique bath vanity cabinet for YOU. Painted in one color of your choice, shabby chic distressed. Antique converted vanities are trending! They are showpieces for 1800 and early 1900 Victorian farmhouse and brown stone renovations ~ powder rooms, guest baths and master baths. Put them in all your bathrooms! They look fab with marble stone or granite, old fashioned faucets and vessel or inset sinks! We provide the cabinet ready for your plumbing. 500 down to get started, another 500 when we find the piece you love, balance due when vanity is finished, approved and ready to ship.
Here's what one Etsy customer said about her custom dresser to vanity conversion: "Loved my custom vanity. Not only was it exactly what I envisioned, working with these artists was a pleasure. Kind professional and answered all my questions promptly. I will use them again and have already told a friend about them!"  
And another.... "Camille is one of the most efficient and communicative sellers on Etsy and eBay. Always superb packing, good tracking detail, and prompt shipping. PLUS she continually has fabulous, unique items. I am a ten-time repeat buyer. Just can't stay away! "
Reviews: 
https://www.etsy.com/your/shops/RedBarnEstates/reviews?ref=shop_info
 
Sizes vary so let us know size range needed. We may de-construct the piece to make size modifications. 
The pieces we sell are from about the 1920's era. We select pieces with excellent craftsmanship, constructed from strong, old growth wood and life-long durability. 
Interior modifications, depending on the piece's drawer/cabinet placement, include:
1) creating a clear area for plumbing with faux drawer fronts
2) cabinet storage space with doors made from the original drawer fronts
4) removing back and making it installation ready
3) reinforcing frame to hold stone, marble or granite tops. The original wood top will be taken out. Sink vessel, faucets, plumbing and top  are NOT included. Your contractor can better provide those for perfect fits with exact size templates that come with your new hardware.
How our custom order works.... Start now by placing your order. Advise your style preference and size needs. We'll then go to work to find the piece and send photos in its original condition for your approval. Once you approve the piece, we restore, convert, enhance and refinish it in our old fashioned shabby chic style. 
Click on the green button ADD TO CART. At checkout mark payment form as OTHER. This allows order completion without paying in full. A PayPal invoice for the 500 down payment will be sent afterwards or we can take your cc by phone. A 500 down payment is required. If we don't find a piece you love in a reasonable time the down payment will be refunded. 
The process is about 8 to 10 weeks. Finding time is allocated within this timeframe. Status updates and photos are sent throughout the refinishing process. It is a fun process creating your vanity working with Camille! Share your ideas and we'll do our best to fill your dream.
All antique furniture will have characteristic dents and dings here & there. We ensure there are no major faults. We use antique metal pulls and knobs, some with old patinas.
Painting is done by hand and by brush. It takes time and we properly apply multiple coats of paint. No spray paint.  Stock colors are our own blends (see color choices in the dropdown). We will also use your custom 1 color for an additional 50, selected from your local hardware store. Metallic colors and 2-tones are extra, please ask.
PACKING AND SHIPPING: We ship nationwide to your nearest Greyhound PackageXpress station for pick up as the most economical way. Insurance and extreme quality packing always included. Picking up from GPX is fast and easy. Many GPX stations offer station-to-home delivery for a little more money. For additional money FedEx Ground shipping may be available. Please contact us for shipping rates to Hawaii, Alaska and Canada. 
Click and like us on Facebook www.facebook.com/redbarnestates
Pin with us too www.Pinterest.com/CamilleReiner/shabby-chic-group-board/ 
Questions? Text/Talk 405.820.1696 Camille. She's happy to reply ASAP.  
Thank you. We appreciate your business :-)

Product name: Rare early 1970s vintage Quorum Ossie Clark/Alice Pollock sculptural midi dress
Description:
Stunning, almost sculptural midi dress from the legendary London boutique Quorum. Quorum was started by Alice Pollock and was also the home of Ossie Clark. Designs by both Pollock and Clark were also sold with just the Quorum label inside, and I believe that this may well be a rare example of Ossie's more tailored work for Quorum. I absolutely adore the plunge front, fastened with a zip up to the waist but then only with a hook and eye at the bust. And the sides are completely open, giving a sexy flash of ribcage. It's like a sexy Safari outfit!
Measurements:
Bust fairly free due to style. I would guess around 36"-38" - Waist 28" - Hips 38" - Length 47"
Fabric:
Feels like a sort of gabardine. Polycotton mix.
Condition:
One small mark on the front, possibly from a brooch being fastened there. A smudgy mark on one end of the tie belt. Sold as vintage.

Product name: Antique Lace Edwardian Wedding Dress 1910 Brussels Lace Gown Bohemian Bridal Gown Unique Belle Epoque Ethereal Wedding Dress
Description:
Seeing is believing and this ultra feminine slip of a dress (so much lace!) really does need to be seen and held to appreciate just how delicately beautiful and soft it is. 
 The majority of the dress has been expertly hand sewn from intricate Brussels Pointe de Gaze lace in a pale cream with a darker cream flounce to the bottom of the dotted Swiss lace front panel. 
More cotton lace adorns the back and across the shoulders. The sleeves are particularly pretty having a scallop lace trim. 
I think this dress would look amazing with a vintage floor length gauze embroidered veil (I'll be listing one very soon!)
The dress is shown under a blush pink vintage silk slip and this is not included in the sale. I would recommend you wear a silk crepe slip underneath, custom made to the length and colour you require. 
As Edwardian dresses were often worn over longer underskirts, having your own under slip made would allow you to 'lengthen' the dress should it be too short as it is.
In excellent condition. There is a 0.5 inch fine repair to one of the sleeves and a few tiny breaks in the gauze although you need to look very closely to find them as there is so much lace. 
Apologies for the photos - trying to photograph dresses in the dull light of a cold British Winter isn't great :-( but should you need to see more then please just shout out.

Excellent gently used condition.
Just a note. This mouton fur is thick and heavy, it weighs about 5 pounds. It is ideal for cold climates.

The condition is very good with bright colors and only a small crease in the corner which would be covered by a frame.  There is also some edge marks that would also be covered by a frame. The overall condition is very good. It does have P.F. Collier & Sons in the bottom left corner. The size is 9" x 11". This is a beautiful Maxfield Parrish print that would look great in any décor!

Product name: VV Rare Ambrotype Photo WOMAN Civil War Cavalry Soldier
Description:
Original circa 1863 ninth-plate (1/9) ruby ambrotype of a FEMALE Civil War Cavalry soldier. Nice, gold-hand coloring throughout, including a "US" on the belt buckle.
Yes, I truly believe this is a woman disguised as a man. 
Everything about this soldier seems feminine to me: Take a close look at the hair, the jawline, eyes and eyebrows, and mouth, thighs... all very feminine physical features. One or two, I might dismiss, but there are just too many non-masculine features here to overlook. 
In addition, her coat fit doesn't look quite right - it looks a bit "stuffed" to me... possibly to add the appearance of bulk and/or from binding?
Keep in mind women in the CW had to fool people, face to face, into believing that they were men..... you're just not going to find a female CW soldier looking more feminine than this one. If a documented photo of this woman ever comes up in the future, the value of this image would instantly increase many times over.
There were hundreds of female soldiers, on both sides, that disguised themselves as men, including a woman named Mary Owens Jenkins, a PA 9th Cavalry soldier. I'm not saying this is Mary - I could not find a photo of her online. Mary Owens supposedly joined the service to be with a man she loved, William Evans. She used the Alias John Evans. William Evans reportedly died and  Mary/John stays in Service. Abraham Jenkins, whom she did marry, was also in the 9th PA. 
I recommend searching on Google for Women Soldiers of the Civil War By DeAnne Blanton, which should take you to a fascinating website on the topic.
Condition - Very nice. All of the little white dots are just dust particles on my scanner or on the photo glass. The image is super nice, sharp and clear. A small spot by her face, as shown, otherwise absolutely no other issues of note.

Each purchase will be placed in a luxury gift box with a gift tag, with historical & collector's fact sheets wrapped in a scroll which authenticate your purchases. We are happy to design the gift tag to order & print a message for it too. All purchases are shipped with a certificate of authenticity.
The Great Exhibition of 1851 was the catalyst that fueled the Arts and Crafts Movement. The exhibits were described as badly made with excessive ornamentation. The Arts and Crafts Movement reaction to the disappointing exhibits was to encourage high quality 'crafts' of craftsmen and artisans. This movement was noted for simplified natural motifs. In many parts of Europe devotees of this movement had strong negative feelings about the use of machinery in the creation of accessories, furniture and works of art. Craftsmen should work with their hands and be free to express their creativity. These craftsmen would return to using primitive tools to produce high quality simplified pieces which often had the appearance of a pre-industrial age. Today Arts and Crafts pieces are highly collectible. There was no extravagant decoration and they are very beautiful.
This is an Arts & Crafts cigarette case made c. the late 1800s. The case is fully hallmarked 800 silver. This composition of 800 silver lends itself to the creation of dark patina which is particularly pleasing on pieces of this genre. This patina can only improve with age and what a beautiful example this antique silver case is. On the lid and base three Centaurea in bloom with a bud on the lower right hand side. The simplicity and balance of the design so charming which is why this movement has such a following. Push the thumb catch to activate a spring loaded catch. The gilded interior showing the repoussage in reverse. The original gold elastic strap still in place. All clasps and hinges work perfectly. Product name: Art Deco Powder Compact, Zell Fifth Avenue, Silver with Gold Overlay, Clear Rhinestones, Removable Pressed Pat, Made in USA
Description:
An elegant memento from a gentler time.
This mid century Zell 5th Avenue powder compact has a lovely silver tone lid highlighted with an art deco style gold tone overlay and three faceted rhinestones. The base is finished in a continuous engine turned wave pattern and is signed USA in the center circle.
The compact opens to reveal a mirrored lid, a powder puff signed Zell Fifth Avenue, a sifter and a full pat of pressed powder.  
The powder pat is removed by inserting a bobby pin or pointed instrument into the groove on the right side of the golden rim and lifting. It is replaced by moving the golden lever under the mirror and inserting the new pat.
The well was also designed to hold loose powder.
CONDITION - Please zoom in on the images to examine.
- The mirror has some age spots near the top center. You can see them in images 3 & 4.
- The base has wear and scratches (Image 5)
- The lid has some black wear spots (Image 1)
Very good vintage condition otherwise.
Measurements:
Outer - 3.25 inches / 8.2 cm in diameter.
Inner powder well - 2.5 inches / 6.4 cm in diameter.
Zell Fifth Avenue
With many of it's former 5th Avenue counterparts [including Rex, Columbia and Dorset], Zell was a big name along 5th Avenue when it came to powder compacts. These companies with “Fifth Avenue” appended to their names were often called “the Fifth Avenues”

Product name: Vintage Stratton Compact Mirror Scone Regal Corona Plaid Celluloid
Description:
DESCRIPTION
Vintage Stratton compact mirror with black felt pochette.  Red and green plaid fabric under celluloid or plastic.  Gold tone.  3” round shape known as the Scone, Regal, or Corona.  The embossed edge leads me to believe that this is most likely a Scone.  For use with loose powder.  Original powder sifter.  Original package insert stating, “keep this Stratton compact in the pochette provided please”.  Stratton’s patented self opening inner lid with the Stratton compact in hand logo.  Mirror with frame marked, “Stratton made in England”.  Spiral base.  Likely dates to the 1950’s.  
An excellent addition to a vintage Stratton collection or vintage compact collection.  A nice holiday gift.
DIMENSIONS
This Stratton compact is approximately 3” in diameter by 5/16”.
CONDITION
Nice and clean with no powder residue.  Some small spots of tarnish.  The mirror is functional but does have a bit of a fog.  Please see photo four.  Sifter and puff are present and in good condition with no evidence of use.  The black felt pochette is in good condition with some loose threads.  The push button clasp and self opening mechanism both work well.

Product name: Vintage Samsonite Red Hard Shell Slim Briefcase Attache No Key - Rare Retro- VGC
Description:
This is the first "Red" Samsonite Hard Shell Slim Attache this shop has had the pleasure to list. About seven months ago I acquired a baby blue hard shell slim Samsonite attache. Before then I had never seen these Samsonite in anything but grey, brown, and black. That acquisition got me started looking for more colorful Samsonite attaches. The baby blue case has sold but since then I have acquired other colors such as pink, red and misty green. It turns out these are very popular so it's unlikely this will last long. So far I haven't found any more of these to acquire but I am looking. In the meantime it may be a while before we can list another.
This is a very unique red textured hard shell slim Samsonite attache / briefcase with silver trim. It is very similar to the first briefcase I owned which was a gift from my Aunt when I graduated from law school in 1976. Mine was ( and Is- I still own it) a medium grey textured hard shell. I've seen plenty of these cases since I started practicing law but this is the first one I've seen in pink. Most are grey, brown or black. 
This case has silver trim with dual keyed latches. The latches have locks and will open and close but there is no key. The interior lining of this case is as unique as the exterior color. It appears to be a pattern of red sunflowers on a dark blue lining. That pattern might take this bag back to the 60's but I am unable to verify the exact age. There is a fan file inside along with a zippered pouch the same red color as the exterior. 
Dimensions:
Length: 17 inches
Height: 12 inches
Width: 2 3/4 inches
Condition:
This case is in very good condition. It has no rips, tears or holes and is structurally sound. This case is in much better condition than many of the Samsonite bright color cases we sold. However, there are some scuffs and scratches on either side that appear as a white color against the pink exterior. There are also a some marks and peeled  chrome trim. Please see photos for best depiction of the condition of this case.
Although, I recently sold this baby blue Samsonite 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/482649937/vintage-samsonite-baby-blue-hard-shell?ref=shop_home_active_1
 I have listed a pink  Samsonite hard shell slim attache which is still available at the time I am listing this red one. 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/498115754/spring-sale-vintage-samsonite-pink-hard?ga_search_query=samsonite&ref=shop_items_search_1

https://www.etsy.com/shop/ProVintageGear
 for similar products from high end manufacturers.

Description:
Vintage Pale Caramel Brown leather Doctors Briefcase, vintage condition, large zip pouch on reverse, working original English lock with key, large central compartment which divides in to three sections.
Size   width  17 inches  (43.25cm)

I come across only a few of these types of English Briefcase's/Doctors bag but I have never seen one in this colour ever. In the past, we have sold some examples of this style of briefcase where people want to use them as part of a vintage display and there is nothing wrong with that but this case will provide good service for a long time to come if wanted for daily use. It has had all the products we use to enrich and nourish the leather and of course I am biased but when a shining example such as this shows up and I measure it against brand new similar types of the same value, there is no comparison and thank goodness for 'Etsy' for a platform to find an appreciative buyer who may feel the same?

Ray-Ban Changeables Sunglasses
While the rest of the sunglass world was stuck in constant density lens technology, a revolution in photochromatic lens technology was taking place at B&L Ray-Ban. The result would be Ray-Ban Changeables lenses in six different tint colors. All the Ray-Ban Changeables lenses self adjust to the brightness of sunlight, but they also darken an extra degree in colder temperatures. And your colder temperatures are typically found at higher altitudes where there is less atmosphere to block both visible and UV light which means that the brighter light of winter sports is taken into account and the lenses adjust accordingly.
Ray-Ban Changeables sunglasses incorporate these innovative Bausch & Lomb photochromatic lenses that react to the sun's brightness to protect your eyes in all light conditions. Regular Ray-Ban Changeables sunglasses darken to compensate for varying outdoor light conditions. Ray-Ban Super Changeables darken even more for stronger light conditions and more sensitive eyes, and both Changeables and Super Changeables filter out 100% of harmful UV rays that can harm your eyes. This change in lens density which results in the lightening and darkening is a lifetime feature of these B&L Ray-Ban lenses and will not disappear or weaken over time.
Ray-Ban Changeables sunglasses darken to 75% of their full capacity within the first minute of exposure to sunlight. Out of sunlight, they lighten half way within the first 10 minutes and about 75% within the first 90 minutes. When new, Ray-Ban Changeables sunglasses and lenses require a breaking in period of several complete darkening / lightening cycles to bring them up to their normal performance. Changeables lenses were also heat treated to make them very impact resistant, but they are not shatterproof or breakproof nor do they have the extreme scratch protection characteristic of Ray-Ban Diamond Hard lenses. B&L Ray-Ban Changeable photochromatic lenses were made to the same standards of optical excellence for which B&L was always known.
One of the rarest forms of original Bausch & Lomb Changeables lenses were the B&L Changeable Rose lenses. They automatically adjust both color and density for varying light levels, excellent for skiing, sailing, boating, and other sports that require sharp vision in all weather conditions. They appear light rose on overcast days to cut through haze and sharpen details. In brigh sunlight, they appear a warm dark gray with rose hues to give superior protection from glare and improve contrast. Changeable rose lenses provide excellent UV protection at all light levels with visible light transmittance of 65% in their lightest state to 17% in their darkest state. Changeable rose lenses were also produced in very small quantities with a full mirror coating applied to the front of the lenses which added even more glare blocking power to allow visible light absorption of 62% to 88% depending upon their photochromatic state.
Following the sale of the Ray-Ban brand to Luxottica in 1999, Bausch & Lomb ceased making Changeables lenses for Ray-Ban sunglasses and they ceased to be offered in the original form.
As an example, a vintage 1/10 12K GF indicates a frame with gold content of about 5% pure gold when you exclude the plastic parts, lenses, and screws. To be more exact, the frames are 5% pure gold, 2.5% copper for wear resistance to the gold finish, 2.5% silver to retain the yellow color of pure gold, and the balance magnetic steel in the core. The "GF" hallmark does in fact mean "Gold Filled," but when you consider the relatively small percentage of gold the frames contain and the fact that the gold is on the surface of the frame rather than the core you can see that the GF marking is somewhat a misnomer. It should also be noted that the "GF" mark is equivalent to the "G.O." (Gold Overlay) mark and the "RGP" (Rolled Gold Plate) mark all used at different periods. Each of these marks implies a gold content of at least 5% by weight. In this type of plating, a layer of gold is attached to the core metal by a combination of pressure, heat, and chemicals. This is the origin of the "Rolled" in RGP, i.e. the gold is literally rolled or pressed onto the core metal. This method differs from electroplating in that the gold content in electroplating is less than 1% by weight. The idea behind RGP is to put enough gold on the core metal such that there will be no wear through at least 30 years of wear. Obviously the process is better than expected as we've never seen a vintage B&L Ray-Ban gold filled frame with wear through to the finish. The bottom line is that a GF finish will last indefinitely with no significant wear to the gold plating at all. Remember that a 12K gold alloy of 50% gold, 25% copper and 25% silver has a hardness rating of 160. That's pretty hard compared to pure gold which has a hardness rating of just 20.

Product name: Arnold Pen Company Marbleized Fountain Pen Old Stock
Description:
Vintage Arnold Pen Company marbleized green, red, gray and orange screw cap fountain pens in very good, never used condition (these are actually old stock).  The pens are 100% original and un-restored.  We have no way of testing the bladder but the fill lever appears to work fine.  Nib is in excellent condition with no wear.  These pens are not guaranteed to be functional without restoration and should be purchased for their value as collectibles.  Add one of these great pens to your personal collection or as gift for that special pen collector in your life.  The pen in the picture may not be the exact pen that you will receive; however, you will receive one of the same color and quality.  Pens are sold individually.     
A little background history:
1935-2005
The Arnold pen company was started  by Remmie Arnold in 1935. Remmie Arnold had worked for the Edison Pen Co and left to start his own company. He knew that their was a large market for low priced fountain pens and he built his pen company into one of the largest fountain pen companies in the world. His pens sold at dime stores and discount stores all of the country [and many other countries]. Most of his pens were priced from 19 cents to 89 cents. He did sell some pens with gold nibs, but they are very hard to find today [they sold for one dollar]. 
Most of the Arnold line were lever fillers. Pen pencil combos were probably their biggest seller. 
Although the Arnold pens were not high priced, they did come in some great colors and they were made fairly well. They have plated trim and most have gold plated nibs. The main interest in them today is for their varied colors. (Courtesy of pensandwatches.com)
After 75 years of faithful production the Arnold Pen Company shuttered the factory and closed it's doors after producing the companies final pens in February 2010.

Saint Augustine had just arrived to Milan to serve as a Professor of Rethoric and was shocked to discover that the clergy would not fast on Saturdays as was usual in Rome. When he asked Saint Ambrose, the Bishop of Milan, for explanation, and it was then that the Saint told him that one should follow the customs of the places one visits, adapting oneself to the people around him or her.

The Roman road system was so vast and efficient that one could truly say that any road would lead to Rome. Today, the expression suggests that different methods can all lead to the same outcome or solution.
To fiddle while Rome burns. Some historians credit Nero as the initiator of the fire that he used a pretext to persecute the Christians, while others dismiss the story as a myth. In any case, the idiom is still used today to rebuke someone who is idle in the midst of an emergency.

Product name: An authentic Judean Widow's Mite Mentioned by Jesus Christ, One of Those Pictured Here - Over 2000 Years Old!!!
Description:
Offered is a  very nice bronze Judean Widow's Mite coin, also called a Prutah in larger size and Lepton in smaller size; and mentioned by Jesus Christ.  The Widow's Mite is the most fascinating of the New Testament coins. The mite or was the smallest of the bronze coins in Jewish currency. This “Widow’s Mite” coin is a genuine bronze coin issued by King Alexander Jannaeus, the Great Grand Nephew of Judah Macabee and the Jewish leader of the Holy Land from 103-76 B.C. It is this type of coin that circulated in the Holy Land during Jesus’ life.
The two dominant symbols that are found on the coin are an anchor and a star with 8 rays. Occasionally Greek lettering is seen on these coins around the anchor illustrating the prevalence of Greek cultural influence that was evident during Jannaeus’ reign.
Judean coins were made by striking long, thin strips of blank metal between two dies. The first coin on the strip was then placed between the two striking dies and hit with a hammer. The strip was then quickly pulled until the next coin was in place and the process repeated. When the strip was completed the coins were cut apart.
The “Widow’s Mite” Biblical coin refers to the story of the poor widow whom Jesus Christ commended in the Temple for having given all she had, two “mites”.
"And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld how the people cast money into the treasury: and many that were rich cast In much. And there came a certain poor widow, and she threw in two Mites...and he called unto him his disciples, and saith unto them, Verily I say unto you, that this poor widow hath cast more in, than all they which have cast into the treasury: for all they did cast in of their abundance; but she of her want did cast in all she had."
Mark 12: 41-44
THERE IS ALSO MENTION OF THE WIDOWS MITE IN LUKE 21: 1-4
There are 2 different Widows Mites.
Lepton Widow’s Mite 103-76 BC (Widow’s Mite “lepton” as mentioned in scriptures) minted under Alexander Jannaeus
Prutah Widow’s Mite 103-76 BC (Often currently referred to as the Widow’s Mite but was a larger coin with similar markings to the lepton( minted under Alexander Jannaeus.
These coins were minted by the Maccabees in Jerusalem and used in Jerusalem during the life of Jesus and the disciples. It was the penny of that time period and is famously mentioned in the New Testament.
There are no two coins of this kind alike! They were minted by hand over 2000 years ago and were in circulation for many years, causing many Prutah and Lepton coins that are found today to be in poor condition.  The coin you receive will be one of the coins pictured here.  Enjoy, what a great gift idea!.  Like all my ancients this will come with a Certificate of Authenticity and lifetime money back guarantee, so buy with confidence!

Product name: Irish Christmas Gift Stocking Stuffer Half Penny Halfpenny Ha'Penny Coin (2nd Bonus Coin FREE!)
Description:
'Christmas is coming, the goose is getting fat. Please put a penny in the old man’s hat. If you haven’t a penny, a ha’ penny will do. If you haven’t got a ha’ penny, then God bless you.' 
Among many ‘country’ Irish, the ha’ penny is a traditional little Christmas gift and a gentle reminder of a lesson not to be forgotten: Be thankful for what you have for there is always someone with less. 
The half penny is also a potentially valuable little gift. The bronze ha’ penny was issued only 16 times between 1928 and 1967 and it is no longer in circulation. It is a rare coin and it will, most likely, continue to increase in value over time. 
After decades in circulation, all our ha’ pennies have the expected amount of scrapes, scratches and weather marks but none are bent or badly dinged. No coin has been cut, pierced, drilled, machined or altered in any way which might diminish its current or future value. 
At the same time, each coin has been gently hand cleaned and lightly hand polished. As a result, each coin has an ‘aged’ luster which nicely highlights the original 1928 Percy Metcalfe 'Sow and Piglets’ design on the reverse side of the coin and the iconic Celtic harp on the observe side. 
As a desk ornament, golf ball marker, necklace pendant, key chain fob, wrist bracelet charm or just as an every day lucky pocket piece, the halfpenny is a unique and memorable keepsake or gift, particularly for anyone with even a little bit of Irish ancestry or interest. 
OUR SPECIAL BONUS: We believe in the Irish Penny tradition. And so, we will send along a second 'thank you' halfpenny with your purchase. Your additional ha' penny may be from a different issue year and have a few more scrapes and weather marks but is FREE. So, God bless. 
NOTE: Your halfpennies will be delivered in a beautiful little velvet coin pouch. We can also provide an elegant gift box. (See photos.)
The little pouch is deep green velvet – not velour or velveteen. Each two-by-two-and-a-half inch pouch is large enough for a few coins and perhaps some other personal keepsake. Truth be, our little velvet pouch is a memorable keepsake itself. 
The ‘white swirl’ gift box has a 'soft' fiber bed and is about three-and-a-half inches square – large enough for the ha' pennies, velvet pouch and a personal note or card.  
(See PACKAGING OPTIONS for pricing.)
And just so you know, with every Irish halfpenny we also send along our best wishes and an everlasting bit of Irish luck… which certainly can’t hurt in these days and times.  
Slainte.

Product name: Queen Anne Victorian Dollhouse, Dolls & Miniatures, Art and Collectibles
Description:
This Queen Anne Victorian Double Bay San Franciscan Row House Dollhouse is a collectible gem!  The house is wired 12 volt.  It was created by a local Wisconsin woodworking artist.  He modeled the dollhouse from a picture of a real house standing in the historical district of the city of San Francisco.  The original houses in this district are today sometimes referred to as "Painted Ladies".  Indeed it is pictured in the book called Painted Ladies.
The dollhouse is made of wood and has interior framing like a real house.  It is in mint condition.  Overall the height is 52 inches high by 24 inches wide by 18 inches deep.  The entire front façade opens on brass hinges that are on the left side as you face the dollhouse.  The two garage doors open as well as a door under the porch stairs and the two front house doors open.  The eleven windows are double hung with plexi glass inserts that look as though they open and close.  
No detail is spared on this dollhouse.  All the corbels, Victorian gingerbread trim, tapered front door columns, scalloped fish  scale tower shingles, lightning rod on top of the asphalt roof shingles, under eaves trim,  inverted green shell trim above the front doors, transom 'leaded' window above 'leaded' front doors, eight pane each windows on the garage doors, handrails on porch steps as well as a horse head hitching post,  wood siding, porch wood plank floor, medallions, brass letter plate slot and brass doorknobs, and is painted in a soft gold historical color.
And, that's just the outside!
Oh, by the way the dollhouse can sit flat on a table ( it has small round rubber buttons on its bottom) or this very special dollhouse can be hung (hooks on the back) on a wall as you are seeing it in the pictures.
Now, as I said the entire front hinged façade swings open to reveal the interior.  There are four rooms, an attic and the interior of the garage.  The fourth room is of course, the foyer that the front doors open into.
The dollhouse is wired 12 volt via a transformer and a cord that comes out of the back of the house with a rocker switch to turn the lights off and on without plugging and unplugging the cord from your real house outlet.  So, the lights that come with the dollhouse are all the small bulbs that are ceiling mounted toward the front of the rooms and in the middle of the attic and garage ceilings.  The hanging front porch light is also included.  The two chandeliers are not included.
Please note that there are pictures, a gold wall mirror and porcelain hand painted plates, a cameo, a flower swag, a mounted butterfly collection...these items are glued on the walls and so they will come with the dollhouse.  
Two of the rooms are wallpapered and one is painted.  There is wood wainscoting in three of the rooms along with cornice and baseboard trim.  NOTE:  above I mentioned the dollhouse's overall measurements.  The interior rooms are 7 1/2 inches deep.  No furniture is included nor any accessory that might be in a picture but not expressly listed in the dollhouse description.  Please ask if you have questions.
ALSO,  I can email you additional pictures of the dollhouse inside and outside, close ups, etc.  Just ask.  Obviously the five pictures I am allotted for this listing do not show all that this dollhouse offers.
Too, as with my other shop listings I can work with you on purchase installments if you wish.  
ALSO,  the shipping charge will be determined when I find out where the dollhouse will be going.  So far, I figure I will be shipping it UPS insured and that I will have a UPS pack and ship center do the packing and boxing.
This is a one of a kind dollhouse that was not made from a kit but, was built from scratch by a skilled wood worker.  It is very unique, it is a collector's dollhouse meant to be an heirloom.

Product name: Horses FDC 1978 - 4 UK stamps, British Post Office first day cover, shire horse, Shetland pony, Welsh pony, thoroughbred, stamp collecting
Description:
An attractive Post Office first day cover featuring horses -  shire horse (9p), Shetland pony (10 1/2p), Welsh pony (11p) and thoroughbred (13p) - postmarked on the day of issue, 5th July 1978.  
The Horsmonden postmark is relevant to the subject of this cover as the name derives from the Anglo Saxon for 'horse farmer valley', and the village is also the site of an annual horse fair.
The unaddressed envelope contains the original printed insert with information about the horses, and about the stamps and first day cover.  It also includes a reproduction of an illustration by Norman Thelwell.
The stamps were designed by Patrick Oxenham and the first day cover by Collis Clements.

Product name: Antique Tambour Lace Parasol Cover, 39" x 35" Oval, Victorian Lace for Home Decor, Costume Use,  Textile Lace Study or Cutter Piece
Description:
This is a lovely Ecru Tambour Lace Parasol Cover from a Victorian era lady's parasol.  It has been, rather mercilessly, run through the washer and dryer, just to see if it was up to the challenge ... and it is.  There is a center hole that would have slipped over the point of the parasol, held in place by the umbrella's finial.  The lady's maid would have tacked it down with discreet stitches so it was held in place.  It would have been used as a fancy upgrade to an existing parasol for special occasions.  As ladies no longer carry parasols, ahem, it is ready for use in your creative project.  It could be used to make a stunning neckline ruffle for an off-the-shoulder bridal, evening, or historical reenactment costume dress.
This parasol cover is decorated with an exuberant collection of leafy, vining scrolls, swoops, and curlicues which continues out in concentric 'circles' to the slightly scalloped edge.  Being an antique piece, it has some stains, four areas repaired by darning, and some breaks in the tambour netting; all of these are in line with its age.  As to be expected, the most damage is at the very center of the piece, where it would have been handled the most.  It is oval in shape, rather than circular.
This item will ship out in a rigid cardboard 9x12 mailing envelope, sent via USPS First Class Package Services.  It is possible to send multiple lace listings in the same envelope, so please convo me prior to purchase if you wish to do so.

Product name: 1963 Studebaker Avanti Fiberglass 72 Speed Records
Description:
An awesome vintage classic car auto print!
Know someone into the fab classic milestone cars of the 1940s - 1960s? This will be a gift not soon forgotten.
A quality and totally gorgeous vintage print of your favorite classic car!
This print is 35 years old.
    * Up for sale is: 1981 print of a painting by William J. Sims: (following written at time of printing, 1981) "1963 Studebaker Avanti. In the early 60s, Studebaker Packard Company president Sherwood Egbert knew his company was in serious trouble. The Avanti, a dramatic departure from the Studebakr's family sedans, was his attempt to avert the company's imminent demise. Limited production of the Avanti, along with its coke bottle profile, facilitated the use of fiberglass for the car's body. The interior, an innovative design, resembling aircraft flight decks, featured an array of instruments, control levers and overhead switches. The Avanti was chosen a Milestone Car for its innovation, engineering and performance, which was admirable: At Bonneville Salt Flats races, Avantis set 72 speed records. Although Studebaker Packard's financial problems caused production to cease in December 1963, the Avanti was so popular that a group bought that division of Studebaker and moved it to Canada..." This description was taken verbatim from what was written when these prints were made. It appears sometimes they did not get all the facts correct. The following was sent to me via email: "In your ad decription you stated that the Avanti division of Studebaker was purchased and moved to Canada. This is incorrect. It is true that Studebaker did move it's production facility to Canada but no Avantis were ever built in Canada. Nate Altman founded the Avanti Motor Corp. and continued to build the Avanti in South bend Indiana. The car had the same basic design as the Studebaker models, but the hand built ones beginning with the 1965 model had Chevy engines. The company was eventually sold and production moved to Youngstown, Ohio."
    * Approximate overall size is 23.5" x 13.5". Nearly Two Feet wide! .
 
    * Signed: by the artist in the print. These were printed to go along with the calendar printed for 1981. v
    * Condition of this item: NMint, stored flat in archival quality sleeves.
    * An original vintage classic car auto print that will be a memorable gift or just a fantastic addition to your collection of classic cars.

Product name: 1900's Tall Antique Tortoise Shell or Celluloid 'Peineta' Spanish Hair Comb-for 'Mantilla'
Description:
This is circa early 1900's antique tall hair comb usually associated with Spain. The description says 'tortoise shell or celluloid' but is either of the two. My description of tortoiseshell is due to the fact that the top part of the comb has been painstakingly carved by hand. The design has been meticulously carved to come up with this intricate design. However, it is also a time when celluloid was at its last stage of usage and soon after the use of celluloid would be replaced by the new plastic invention called Bakelite. This came as an antique piece that have come from England but is most likely a hair comb that was made in France (as per my readings from other sellers) and has been made to cater to Spanish customers. The scroll design very much reflect the intricate design of Spain. The center of the top piece of the comb also suggest the shape of a family crest.
This comb is called 'peineta' in Spanish (similar to the way it would be pronounced in English: pei as in pay (ex: payment); ne (as in Netherlands); ta (as in talcum). A 'peineta' cannot be understood without understanding the word: 'mantilla'. The Spanish alphabet consist the letter 'll' (double letter L) and is called 'elle' (pronounced as in: el, ye). The 'peineta' is thus a Spanish or Spanish-influenced decorative hair comb that traditionally is used to hold the 'mantilla' (pronounced as: man-ti-lya or nearest is man-til-ya) which is traditionally a veil or shawl made of lace or silk. An adaptation has occurred afterwards where the peineta is used on its own without the mantilla. The mantilla covers the comb or peineta giving a certain perceived height to the wearer although my analysis suggests that a mantilla over the head does not always need the use of a 'peineta' since a peineta cannot alone support the weight of a long veil and thus some adaptations has been used. We also have to remember that women centuries ago normally had very, very long hair which would help support the peineta and the mantilla. Growing the longest hair was a source of pride amongst those women.
There are dress codes as to the length of the mantilla which can be below the hips or up to floor length. This is more appreciated if one observes the traditional flamenco Spanish dance. There are also social, political and religious significance in the use of this 'peineta'. Further research points to the fact that the wear of 'peineta' and 'mantilla' started in the warmer regions of Spain in the late 16th century and became popular with women in the 17th and 18th centuries. Renaissance Spanish painter Diego Velasquez and 18th century painter Goya depicted the mantilla in their paintings. Queen Isabella II of Spain who reigned from 1833 to 1868 revived the use of mantillas.
Traditionally, the peineta and/or mantilla is a symbol of power, status and position in society. There are 'privilege' rules in Spain as to the use of the mantilla. The use of black or white mantilla was the privilege of the Spanish queens and the nobles. Black mantilla is used for the Holy Week or as an audience to the Pope. White mantilla is reserved for weddings. Black mantilla is for married women and white mantilla is for single women. Today in Spain, the peinetas and mantillas are still used for bullfights, Holy Week, weddings or for an audience to the Pope.
Spain was a country that was attributed to the spread of Christianity in many parts of the world. In many colonised countries of South America and in Asia particularly the Philippines (its population is predominantly Roman Catholic, Christianity was adopted in 1521 and the country is named after King Philip II of Spain), the tradition and influence on the use of 'peineta' and 'mantilla' are very much present. Although, high towering mantillas were not used over the heads of the women, the much smaller version of the mantilla which we would call the veil was used by women as they enter the Church. The use of the mantilla as a shawl is also featured in Spanish-influenced dances. It seem to show that the use of mantilla as a shawl was adapted to the native costume of the Filipino women. Tradition dictated that women cover their heads with a veil upon entering the church and while attending the Mass. The veil was folded as one exited the Church. This tradition was still very much in practice till the late 60's. The practice discontinued but recently I have noticed that women are starting to use veils again (in Australia) while attending Mass. 
The use of 'peineta' is a symbol of status in society in many colonised countries. Women who belonged to wealthy families and whose families would have influential connection to the Church would wear the 'peineta'. The Spanish Galleon Trade in Manila portrayed one of busiest ports in the world from the 1565 to 1815 and thus enabled the exchange of goods coming from the 'natives' (a term used  in the study of colonised countries referring to the indigenous people) of the Phillippine Archipelago, China, India and other parts of Asia. These goods were shipped via the galleon ships to Acapulco, Mexico which were then shipped to Spain. These goods eventually ended up in Europe and vice versa. The opening of the Suez Canal also enabled wealthy people to travel for the first time and thus helped in the exchange of goods between the West, the Far East and other Asian countries. 
Many of the heirlooms including peinetas that belonged to women of high status in Philippine society are still treasured today and kept within the family. Many of these antique peinetas are displayed in museums in different regions of the Philippines. Some antique peinetas are made of solid gold, tortoise shell, horn, pearls, ivory etc. Indeed, the 'peineta' (and the 'manitilla') have come a long way. If one searches the story of the 'peineta' in the South Americas, the story of the peineta and mantilla would be very similar. The peineta (and the mantilla) is one of Spain's legacy to the world.
This 'PEINETA':
This large 'peineta' is circa early 1900's. It could be made of tortoise shell if not celluloid. Whatever it is, this is an authentic piece belonging to that era. The colour is brown, not too dark, not too light. This antique piece bears some signs of slight use and wear commensurate to its age and thus should be appreciated more for it. The top of the comb has been carved painstakingly by hand. The result of this hand carving is therefore irregular which distinguishes it to other forms of peinetas that are more regular in pattern that suggest it is pressed rather than hand carved such as this.
The design suggests Spanish-influenced design which is probably Baroque or Rococo design. The middle part of the design suggest to me a blank shape for a family crest. There are very slight signs of minor and negligible scratches on the obverse and reverse side which confirms to us its use and age.This is a hard material although the comb portion has some form of flexibility. All intricate branches of the scrolls or the overall design are ALL intact. There are no broken parts.
This 'peineta' is a one-off piece in my collection and is in very good antique condition. It deserves to join your collection or possibly use it for your special occasion together with a 'mantilla'. Please take the time to examine the pictures shown.

Product name: 1969 Woodstock fence key chain Creedence Clearwater Revival CCR
Description:
Made from the Original 1969 Woodstock Music Festival Fence!
You are looking at a peace pendant key chain made from part of the original 1969 Woodstock Festival Fence.  Each pendant is hand crafted here in Bethel, NY by artisan Joey Alexy.  The size is 2" diameter.  Own a rare peace of the actual fence that surrounded the Woodstock site in 1969.  Attendees trampled the fence down, and promoters decided to make it a free concert, which was the largest gathering of people in one place at that time.
100 % Money Back Guarenteed REAL!  Includes a certificate of authenticity!
Each of our peace pendants is made using original fence from the 1969 Woodstock Music and Arts Fair in Bethel, NY.  Pendants are shipped with a notorized certificate of authenticity stating that they are in fact made from the actual and genuine Woodstock Fence.  These rare pendants are 100% guarenteed to be made from 40 year old fence that surrounded the Woodstock concert site.  If you are not completely satisfied with your pendant for any reason, please return it to me for a full refund.
Authenticated by The Museum at Bethel Woods!
A section of the Alexy Family's fence is currently on display at the Museum at Bethel Woods, as seen in the photo.  This artifact is the same fence that we use to make these fence pendants.  This Museum has the largest collection of Woodstock Festival memorabilia in the world, and the experts there have authenticated our fence to be the real thing!  Do not mistake Peace Fence products with the multitudes of Woodstock Festival replicas out on the market today, most being sold as real.
Creedence Clearwater Revival played at woodstock on Saturday night, August 16, 1969 from 1:30am -2:15am.  They played the following songs:

Product name: VINTAGE WEDDING HANKIE White Linen Tambour Lace Roses at Each Corner for Friendship & Passion Handmade in Switzerland Excellent Condition
Description:
VINTAGE WEDDING HANKIE White Linen Tambour Lace Roses at Each Corner for Friendship & Passion Handmade in Switzerland Excellent Condition
11 1/2 x 11 1/2 inches
Tambour lace refers to a family of lace made by stretching a fine net over a frame (the eponymous Tambour, from the French for drum) and creating a chain stitch using a fine hook to reach through the net and draw the working thread through the net.
Note that there is one small break in the netting (see last picture).  Priced accordingly.
Laundered, pressed, sized and ready for that special day.  Bright and clean.
A FEW WORDS ABOUT WEDDING HANKIES
Vintage white and ivory hankies that are popular today with wedding parties were produced primarily in the 1940s and ‘50s in places like Madeira, Switzerland, and the Far East.  Embroidery, applique, drawn work, application of lace, and hemming were usually done by hand, often by 2 or more women who would each apply her speciality to the piece.  Sold primarily in Europe and the United States, ladies would always have a clean white hankie at the ready to dab noses, catch tears, or clean a spot off Junior’s face.  It’s said that no lady would let her maid launder her hankies.  (I wouldn’t know, of course.  I’ve never had one - a maid that is.).  Each evening she would wash that day’s hankie in scented facial soap, then smooth it out on her mirror to dry where it would cling until morning.  Try it yourself.  It really works.  Or tell your maid.

Description:
Made of crisp cotton and measuring 12” sq with hand rolled and stitched hems this beautiful vintage handkerchief features  a gorgeous B  monogram  (approximately 3”x3”) created using a variety of hand embroidery techniques;  Running and satin stitch as well as shadow work. (Shadow work is a term used to describe the effect created by placing decorative stitches on the reverse of the fabric, thus creating a ‘shadow “ on the fabric face.)
Dating to the early 1980's when beautiful handwork items of superior quality were still being produced in China.  In the past 30 years or so machine embroidery has become the standard and alas the artistry of hand embroidery is slowly fading into oblivion. It was acquired as part of a large stash of handwork  linens  I acquired from a warehouse in Hong Kong some years ago.  
The handkerchief has been specially folded, tied with white satin ribbon and placed within a protective crystal clear pouch. It is accompanied by a descriptive insert,  with the quote, “Sometimes the best things do come in small packages.”

Product name: Dog Car Seat
Description:
OVERVIEW: WHY CHOOSE SAFETYFUR'ST?
_______________________________________________________________________________________
1) The SafetyFur’st car seat was created specifically for small dogs. It is not merely a scaled down version of a generic pet product.  This car seat is designed to meet the unique needs of small and teacup breeds.  The car seat in this listing is recommended for dogs below 9 pounds.  For dogs weighing 10-15 pounds, a larger model is listed in my shop.  If your dog weighs more than 15 pounds, I would recommend the Pupsaver line of car seats which is available through Amazon.
2) In an accident or sudden stop, the high front panel of a SafetyFur'st car seat works like a catcher’s mitt preventing your dog from being thrown from the car seat. Most other dog car seats rely on a harness or collar to restrain the dog which concentrates the impact of the collision on the dog’s chest or neck making them inappropriate for the delicate bone structure of small dogs.
3) In the SafetyFur’st, the dog is restrained by the foam padding rather than a harness, so the impact is spread evenly across the dog’s body. The purpose of the harness tether in the SafetyFur'st is to prevent the dog from roaming. 
4) The SafetyFur’st car seat contains no hard parts to injure your dog in an accident. It is made from fabric and a mixture of foams.
5) The SafetyFur’st car seat requires no installation—simply wrap the seat belt around the car seat and close the Velcro tabs around the seat belt.  Then, attach the tether to your dog’s harness and you and your furry friend are ready to travel.
6) The SafetyFur’st car seat is designed to provide some protection even when used without a seatbelt. Most dog car seats work only when properly installed, which can lead to inconsistent use. When used without a seatbelt, the weight of the SafetyFur’st along with the nonslip bottom keeps it in place under ordinary driving conditions. In an accident or sudden stop, the car seat slides forward into the floorboard, allowing energy to dissipate. As the front panel contacts the dash, it folds over the car seat like a lid encompassing the dog in a foam cocoon and providing protection from flying debris.
7) The SafetyFur’st car seat can be used in the front seat or in the back seat.
8) When you arrive at your destination, the SafetyFur'st car seat can easily be removed from your car to serve as your dog's "Away from Home Bed." 
PRODUCT DESCRIPTION:
_______________________________________________________________________________________
The SafetyFur'st small dog car seat was designed by dog lovers for dog lovers. SafetyFur'st's goal is to make car travel safer and more comfortable for small dogs while providing ease of use for the owner to facilitate the consistent use of the car seat. 
The SafetyFur'st can be used in the front seat or the back seat. No installation is required. The seat belt wraps around the car seat much like a passenger and the tether attaches to your dog’s harness. Vecro tabs on either side of the car seat can be wrapped around the seatbelt for additional security. The bone shaped handle makes moving the car seat between the front seat and the back seat a breeze.
The SafetyFur’st car seat contains no hard parts to injure your dog in an accident. It is made from a mixture of foams with a fabric cover. The sides and the back are constructed from 1-inch high density foam. The high front panel contains 3 layers of foam strategically arranged to both cushion and restrain. On the inside, 3-inch memory foam panels surround the interior space. The base of the car seat is made from a dense 4-inch furniture-grade foam for structure and strength.
In the event of a collision or sudden stop, the high front panel works like a catcher’s mitt, preventing your dog from being ejected from the car seat. The dog is restrained by the foam sides of the car seat which spreads the impact across the dog’s body. Most dog car seats rely on a harness or collar to stop the forward momentum of the dog in a crash which concentrates the impact on the dog’s chest and/or neck making them inappropriate for the delicate bone structure of a small dog.
The SafetyFur’st car seat works most effectively when used with a seatbelt and the harness tether attached; however, it still provides significant protection when used without the seat belt or harness. When used without a seat belt, the weight of the car seat and the nonslip bottom keep it in place under ordinary driving conditions. In an accident or sudden stop, the car seat slides forward into the floorboard, allowing energy to dissipate. As the front panel contacts the dash, it folds over the car seat like a lid encompassing the dog in a foam cocoon and providing protection from flying debris. *When the car seat is used without a seatbelt, it is important to move the front seat of your car far enough forward to ensure that the car seat will contact the dash and fold over before sliding to the floor.
When not in use, the SafetyFur'st can be stored in the backseat or on the floorboard. The foam-construction contains no hard parts, so in the event of an accident, the car seat won't become a dangerous projectile. 
The SafetyFur'st is designed specifically for small dogs. It is intended for passengers weighing 9 pounds or less. The interior measures 12" by 11". This creates a snug fit for most dogs but leaves ample space for a small dog to sit down, lie down, or curl up in a ball.  The purpose of the car seat is to restrain the dog in the event of an accident, so extra space is not necessary or desirable.  The outside of the car seat is 14" wide, 13" deep, and 10" tall. The higher front panel is 19" tall. 
The memory foam insert facing the driver's side is lower to allow the dog a comforting view of the driver. The lower driver's side and scooped cutout also make self-loading possible for many dogs. A side pocket was added to hold travel essentials such as a harness and leash. The passenger side memory foam insert is taller to protect against side impact.
Dogs seated on leather/vinyl seats or those caged in plastic or metal dog carriers can slide around causing panic and increasing the likelihood of injury or motion sickness. The cloth and foam interior of the SafetyFur'st holds the dog in place.
The SafetyFur'st is not a booster seat. The bottom rises only 4 inches above the seat of the car, so it does not provide a continuous view for the dog, but keeping the car seat lower, increases safety and stability. In addition, while some dogs appreciate the view that a booster seat provides, many others are frightened by being suspended above the seat.
For cleanliness and comfort, a removable bedding insert in included. The bedding insert is machine washable and is filled with cotton batting and loose stuffing. It is reversible for seasonal comfort. One side is covered in soft fur and the other side in a cotton fabric. Additional bedding inserts are available for purchase.
For additional information, please send a message or call, 405-476-7325.

Product name: Bird Chew Toy
Description:
A healthy bird is a happy bird- and these chew toys are designed to cover both!
Made from native Australian eucalyptus and your choice of either stainless steel wire or natural kangaroo leather. You also have the choice of wood pieces, just bark pieces or wood plus bark pieces. Wood pieces have been dyed with watered down food dye to provide visual stimulation for your bird while also being safe to chew!
We offer these chew toys in a range of lengths (please also let us know what kind of bird you have upon checkout so we can send you a toy with suitable sized wood or bark pieces). Our chief product tester Lori the rainbow lorikeet is currently using a long piece as a chew toy, perch and head scratcher!
Why choose our products?:
*Eucalyptus is safe for most birds, especially those native to Australia! (please check with your avian vet just to make sure for your particular species of bird though!). Plus it's a hard wood so your toys will last quite a while!
*Any metal used is stainless steel-cheap galvanised wire could cause metal poisoning in birds, so we only use metal that does not cause this!
*We use naturally finished leather to ensure no chemical poisoning occurs in your bird. We avoid string as these fibres can be swallowed and cause impactions (particularly in nectar eaters such as lorikeets!)
*Wood and bark is collected from areas with minimal to no risk of pesticide exposure
*Designs are tested by our own birds before we sell them-if they have fun with them we're sure your bird will too!
*Toys are completely handmade from natural wood branches and bark, ensuring you have carefully created and unique toys to keep your bird interested! As such, the shape and size of the wood and bark pieces in the product you receive may differ slightly from the images, but the design of the toy will be the same.

Description:
🐕 Solid Oak Pet Memorial Frame 🐕
Our handcrafted shadow frame is made to hold your most valuable memories of your special pet. Made from solid oak, the frame can hold a number of little treasures such as a collar, toy, paw print, picture or special message - saying how you feel about them.
The frame pictured is the one we created for our own little dog, which we want to remember everyday. 
WHAT YOU GET:
It incorporates a solid oak frame, solid wood box, hinges, clasp, backing board, front mount, collar hanger, picture mount and a professionally engraved plaque. 
Every part of the frame is carefully handmade and fully underpinned to ensure it will last a lifetime. 
SIZE:
We can make the frame to any size and specification you require for your own pet. Simple message us with all of your ideas and we will discuss size, woods, finishes etc.

🐕 H: 26cm (10'')

The glazing is made from high quality acrylic (perspex), which is much lighter and damage resistant than glass. the frame opens via 2 small decorative hinges, and locks using a brass clasp for extra safety.
