Product name: Cold pressed coconut oil best quality premium extra virgin coconut oil natural organic coconut oil 4 oz
Description:
D.Medicine Woman's best oil for organic skin and hair care or silky smooth massage! We selected this cold pressed extra virgin coconut oil because not only is it USDA certified organic coconut oil, it retains 100 percent of it's excellent therapeutic value, making it the natural healthy choice for organic skin and hair care. Works great for dry skin, sunburn, and for daily skin maintenance. This coconut oil is so light and clean, you can even use it for cooking, or internally to enjoy it's many therapeutic benefits.
No, we don't make this oil ourselves, but we do purchase bulk amounts from a local supplier right here on the Big Island of Hawaii. These folks have family in American Samoa, where coconuts abound, and working together they harvest, press, and ship this wonderful oil right here to Hawaii. They work hard to let us know when the shipment will be arriving so that we can get it right away, assuring that this extra virgin coconut oil is the freshest available!
So what makes it virgin?
What makes coconut oil virgin is that it is pressed from the coconut milk. Our organic coconut oil is produced using the wet process. Coconut milk is made first. Fresh coconut kernel is shredded, mixed with a little water, and then squeezed or pressed to extract the oil. The resulting oil/water mixture produces coconut cream or coconut milk depending on the percentage of oil. The coconut milk is then allowed to separate naturally. Since oil is lighter than water, it rises to the surface. This usually takes about 24 hours and then the oil can then be skimmed off. No heat or chemicals are needed in this process, and so that this extra virgin coconut oil retains 100% of it's original aroma and taste, along with all the good stuff that makes it such a healthy choice. And because no heat was used to extract it, it has a longer shelf life (years) and requires no refrigeration. What's left after pressing out the virgin oil is the now nearly dry coconut meat, or "copra". The copra is what you use to put on cake or ice cream as coconut flakes. They also use it to make less expensive coconut oil, by using heat, and/or chemical solvents to extract the last of the coconut oil. Oils extracted from the copra using this method have no taste or aroma, or therapeutic value. That's why here at D.Medicine Woman, we only recommend and sell natural virgin coconut oil.
So what about "extra virgin"?
This is a term that was borrowed from the olive oil industry. There isn't really an "extra virgin" when it comes to coconut oil. A lot of folks still call natural organic coconut oil "extra virgin" and so we still retain the term in our description so they'll know that this is the good oil they've been searching for!
Coconut oil has the distinction of being closest in molecular make-up to your body's own natural sebum (the natural oil in your skin), making it more readily absorbed into your skin and also ideal for use in organic skin care and as a absorbed into your skin and also ideal for use in organic skin care and as a super healthy massage oil. Coconut oil also contains 47% lauric acid, second only to the amount of lauric acid found naturally in human mothers milk.
Coconut oil is fully metabolized by the body, and unlike most oils, Is not absorbed into the fatty
cells and tissues. It is an ideal carrier for essential oils allowing them to penetrate through the skin's fatty layer and into the blood where they can be most effective. Because of it's light consistency, it will not clog skin pores, making it suitable for use on dry, sensitive, or problem skin. Organic coconut oil is fast becoming the oil of choice for many applications in natural healing. We were so impressed with this oil that we now use it ourselves as one of the primary ingredients in all of our lotions and creams. Since changing over to coconut oil for our creams, we have received excellent feedback about it from our many clients who have tried it!
D.Medicine Woman's virgin coconut oil is certified organic, chemical and toxin free and has virtually no negative side effects on most people, and is easily tolerated by even the most sensitive skin. It also has an SPF 4 rating as a sunblock, and can be used as such for those that only need light protection from the sun. As a massage oil, you'll be amazed at the silky smoothness and glide. And for skin care and maintenance, there's nothing else quite like it!
If you visit our store often, then you may have noticed that sometimes we are all out of this coconut oil. We only purchase it in limited quantities, inorder to assure that we never have any "old stock", so that you can rest assured that what you are purchasing is the freshest available, anywhere!
4 oz Size Bottle
Thank You for choosing D.Medicine Woman!

Product name: Chunky Knit Blanket Chunky Blanket Chunky Knit Throw Blanket Throw Fringe Thick Blanket Afghan Fringe Blanket
Description:
Chunky knit throw blanket in almost any colors (chunky mini blanket with fringe). Features a close knit, tight knit and thick knit 3'x3' square, embellished with foot long fringe on two sides.
This particular version shown first, I hand knit with two slightly different soft, cream colored yarns. Then I added colorful, ethnic Moroccan style fringe that is a mix of neutrals and brights. Neutrals include grey, taupe, cream, brown and charcoal. Colors include yellow, pinks, purples, greens, teal-turquoise, oranges, etc. 
I departed from my usual penchant to add sparkle and bling to the tassels: Other than an occasional "semi gloss" ribbon yarn, the fringe in these thick knit blankets is matte :)
Hand knit with OVER 10,000 stitches by Crickets’ Creations at 
https://CricketsCreations.etsy.com/
SIZE: I use two strong, durable yarns together for the STRETCHY 3 feet x 3 feet (1 metre x 1 metre) square base.  Once I add the fringe on two ends, the blanket measures approximately 3 feet wide x 5 feet long.
The fringe yarns may vary for each blanket (I like to substitute fancier and/or subtly textured yarns whenever possible) and could include purple, orange, creams, blues, reds, greens, grey, black & more. 
This richly colored throw blanket is warm without being suffocating and is the perfect length (about 6 feet or 2 metres long including fringe) to snuggle one person. 
I originally designed this style for a photographer to use in her portrait photography business, although it would look lovely in any naturally styled home.
Not sure about what color blanket would be best?  Samples happily sent worldwide with no charge or obligation (please just message me with your name and mailing address)
My designs are exceptional quality and a great value; this blanket is strong and durable for everyday use, or can really dress up a room.
Only soft, cruelty free, designer, vintage or novelty yarns (vegan). No allergenic animal fibers.
Designed & knit in the clean, fresh, high desert air in the heart of Grand Canyon Country, USA (no perfumes, cigarette smoke or pet odors)
Hand wash in cool water with mild soap. Rinse well. Resist wringing to dry. Dry flat.

Hi, 
My name is Alex Senchenko, I'm abstract artist.
Art as such is a pure reflection of the artist's nature and inner world. I have been always qualified myself as an experimentator and a hunter for new and interesting art techniques, expressions in different mediums and materials. Welcome to my online- gallery!
My name is Edelgard Schroer. I was born in Moers as grandchild of Johann Keuten, a well-known artist in the Niederrhein area. In 2003, after extensive studying and co-working with the designer and artist Jean Pellen in Düsseldorf, I opened my own art gallery. My works cover a wide range of diverse styles from abstract to even floral motives. My style is varied, I do not like to paint within the same medium.
Unique to all of my paintings, you will discover in each one a sensual expression of the joy of living.
My paintings are all one of a kind, no prints or giclees in any kind.
My gallery is located in the heart of the rural country Geldern, close to the Dutch border. Here my work is exhibited in a spacious 120qm area.
I hope, you enjoy the journey through my world of colors and I thank you very much for looking.
If you have any questions, please contact me. I look forward to your mails!

Product name: Original Large Abstract painting   24 X 48 Inches-by Artist JMJartstudio-Saturation-Wall art-wall decor - Orange painting-Oil painting
Description:
Original large abstract canvas painting by JMJartstudio. This wall art measures 24 x 48 inches , it is a orange painting featuring several shades of orange , yellow and white .
My name is Sherri, I love to paint things that I love. If you have passed through my shop you will see that I like to share a little information about each piece that I paint. Everything has a story right ? Inspiration and Ideas are found in the oddest of places sometimes. Often when I think of it myself, I think I must have be crazy. But then I pick my colors begin to paint and the final piece is born. So I wasn't crazy after all. Look what this has become its beautiful bright , cheerful and sure to make you smile every time you pass by it. My inspiration the sole of a flip flop crazy right ?
This is an original piece, I would consider each one of my paintings to be one of a kind . Since it is painted by me each piece I create is different and unique in its own way .I am proud to say all my paintings are Made in America, in my studio in New York each one is hand signed by me the artist.
They are painted on high quality 3/4 inch stretched canvas with a Gallery wrapped edge. What is STRETCHED canvas ? Stretched canvas means the canvas has been stretched and secured on a wooden frame. GALLERY WRAPPED simply means the canvas has been secured and stapled on the back to give the canvas a nice finished edge.This is a great thing since you will not have to buy a frame for your painting, it can be hung up straight from the box.
What will your piece look like when you take it from the box. It will be carefully wrapped in bubble wrap to ensure its safe arrival . Did I mention that all of my pieces are fully insured so there are no shipping worries.OK back to the painting, once you remove the bubble wrap,first thing you will notice is the beautiful protective finish. I want your piece to last for years and years, it also makes it easy to dust. You will see how this finish adds to the beauty of your painting, how the sheen plays off all the texture and movement this piece is made up of.Now if you look closer, you will see how all the colors are blended, to create a rich marriage of light and dark, and how well they work together. This piece will brighten up any room sure to make you smile. .Take a look to the bottom right hand corner here you will see my signature. I sign all my pieces along with the year I created them .On occasion a piece may only be signed on the back . You wonder why ? I do this because I like to leave my clients options.the versatility of hanging your piece vertical or horizontal .This way it can be easily displayed in different areas of your home.
Alright now that you took your treasure from the box what do you do with it ? Its simple, nothing special is needed, just a couple little picture hangers and you are all set.Generally a painting can be hung up within 5 minutes. You might ask why I don't use wire on my pieces ,its plain and simple , over the years I have seen those little wires and hooks create damage.Damage that I'm not willing to risk your painting. It also will leave you that hanging versatility I mentioned above.
I think I have covered everything ,but in case I didn't I would love to hear from you. If you have any questions send them along, want to share your space, ask for a suggestion, I would be happy to see your room. Send me a photo I am always glad to help.This is my favorite part I'm going to ask a favor of you, if you would like to you to share a photo with me, of the painting hanging in your beautiful home. I would love to see it .This is one of my biggest enjoyments !! .

Product name: Custom COUPLE PORTRAIT from SELFIE - Boyfriend gift, girlfriend gift, watercolor painting, special gift from girlfriend, for him, for men
Description:
Custom COUPLE PORTRAIT from SELFIE - Boyfriend gift, girlfriend gift, watercolor painting, special gift from girlfriend, for him, for men
❤ This listing is for 2 people/animals custom watercolor portrait *
( * You can see how accurate is the portrait comparing with the last image that is the original photo.)
Hello! I am Natilles a portraitist watercolor artist from Barcelona. I paint portraits with a very expressive and coloring style. My style is different because the drawing is very realistic, but the color does not, and that's what makes my paintings unique and modern :)
For people who are very hard to surprise I think that a hand painted portrait is the perfect gift. Also for wedding gifts, newborns, birthdays, 50th, 25th wedding anniversary, also paper anniversary (1st wedding anniversary) or memorials it will be a meaningful present.
You can see more examples of my custom portraits below:
https://www.etsy.com/shop/SesCaniques?section_id=13661633&ref=shopsection_leftnav_3
❤ HOW TO PROCEED
You are not buying this portrait: You are buying a portrait 100% personalized. I could paint under your instructions based on your reference photo.
Before or after buying this product (is better before), we will speak through Etsy or email. You can send me the photo that I will use to paint the portrait and also tell me when you need it. Then we talk about the colors you want to use. The high resolution photos allows me to see the finest details and is better to work with and the result is better too.
Closeup photos are good in small and medium sizes (faces and shoulders), half bodies photos (heats to hips) are better in medium sizes and entire bodies photos are good in medium and large sizes.
In my blog I explained with a visual example, the procedure to follow in case you need more information:
http://natilles.wordpress.com/2014/03/31/how-to-order-a-custom-watercolor-portrait-by-natilles/
❤ WHAT I OFFER 
The drawing will be very accurate to the picture and I will keep you informed sending photos of every step of the process. Once the painting is done, I'll send you a final photo for your approval and I can make any final adjustments. I really appreciate the criticism. My goal is that you like it so much. I will make all the changes with pleasure and your opinion always helps to make the portrait better.
❤ THE BACKGROUND, A NUMBER OF CHARACTERS AND EXTRA ELEMENTS
This listing is for TWO people/animals portrait in front of a white background or  background painted with diffuse patches of watercolor. For complex backgrounds (e.g., in a car, on a boat, in a dinning room, in a garden, a cake, etc.) you have to add this listing to your purchase: 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/246505062/
If you would more or less persons or animals you can revise my shop looking for an item with the number of persons do you need, or use this short cuts:
▶ 1 person / animal
https://www.etsy.com/listing/229669527
▶ 2 people / animals 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/241699593
▶ 3 people / animals 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/167216795
If you want to add props (like people with butterflies in his hair, or a lot of flowers surrounding the face), or any photomontage, I’m happily available to do it. Also I’m available to paint other sizes or portraits with more people. In all this cases write me and I will create a special item for you.
❤ SPECIFICATIONS (TECHNICAL, MATERIAL AND CARE) 
TECHNIQUE It is painted by watercolor (high quality and of very concentrated and luminous colors). The brands I use are Holbein Artists and Winsor & Newton Artist. I also use pencil to draw.
The PAPER used is Guarro extra cold pressed. It is the best for watercolors, is 100% cotton, white color & extra thickly (350 g.) The maximum size is  27" x 39".
You can choose the COLORS. But there is one restriction: I NEVER paint with the real tones (the picture realistic tones). I can paint with only one color (monotone) or several; that does not change the price. I can help you with the choice if you want.
I send you the original hand-signed by me. This image will be yours forever and I will be able neither to sell it nor to reproduce it. You can not use the painting for advertising, or make copies or use it for profit of any kind. If you want the painting for something like that, tell me before and I happily sell yo the rights and the digital image.
IMPORTANT: Watercolor can not receive the direct sunlight because it will eventually clarify. The sun beams can not touch the paper.
❤ PROCESS TIME, PACKAGING, SHIPPING
If you require your painting in a certain time frame, please let me know before the purchase.
Maybe I have orders in queue before yours.
If you need a very Express shipping, you can pay the extra cost to update the standard shipping into a Express. You can add this service selecting your country here:

For more information about processing time, packaging and shipping please read my Policies section:

If you still have some doubts about, please do not hesitate to contact me before doing the purchase... I like to receive emails and also respond quickly because I'm almost always online.
Thanks for being reading this :) Note that english is not my natural language, apologize the mistakes.

Product name: Violet Perfume - Using essential oils extracted from fresh flowers, I have created a true Violet fragrance that all will enjoy.
Description:
Violet is fresh and romantic without being overly floral. It has sweet, sharp and crisp green notes.  Violets are considered a good luck gift to be given in any season.  
The violet, the traditional Valentine's Day flower, celebrates modesty, virtue, faithfulness, humility and possible happiness.   According to legend, the Christian priest St. Valentine wrote love notes using ink made from the violets he grew. 
As a fourth-generation perfumer, I left the industry to spend my time with family and friends.  It is my joy and desire to create new versions of traditional scents using fresh flowers that are steam-extracted at the peak of freshness to capture the pure essence of such remarkable creations.  With so many cheap imitations around, I knew there would be a market for pure, natural scents with none of the artificial additives that mass-produced fragrances use.  As a result, I have created scents that wear longer than most without causing irritation to you or others.  I try to be very allergy and asthmatic sensitive in my formulations so more people can enjoy the fragrances.  Each fragrance can be ordered in Normal, Extra, or Light concentration.  
All fragrances are mixed to order.  With natural essential oil perfume, the essence oils take about two weeks to fully open up in the carrier, making it a wonderful journey to see what the final fragrance will be.  Some of my favorite memories of perfuming was working with my grandmother to mix different fragrances and checking them each day to see what new notes I could detect.
If you wish to have an item shipped directly to a gift recipient, you can enter the recipient's mailing address during checkout and indicate that it is a gift in comments.   All fragrances are shrink-wrapped for safety.
Thanks for looking!

Product name: Handmade Shaving Brush with Natural Bristles
Description:
This stylish Hand Crafted Shaving Brush has natural bristles and the handle is made of resin. The brush has been designed to generate extra lather that is sure to enhance your shaving experience. For best results we suggest soaking the brush in hot or warm water for a few minutes before every shave. By doing so the brush becomes softer, retains more water and generates a rich warm lather. 
The performance of a shaving brush depends not only on the quality and type of bristles used but also on how the knots are formed. Since inception we have always built the Knots in-house. The process starts with weighing the bristles to ensure that the knot size is consistent. Once the bristles are weighed we then form the knots using our proprietary jigs designed exclusively for this function. We then complete the formation of the knot by using a special epoxy which ensures minimal loss of bristles. The knots are formed in a way that splays easily allowing the brush to retain water and air needed to create a fuller lather. 
 
Approximate Dimensions: Overall height: 115 mm      Loft: 60 mm      Knot: 22 mm   
We are pleased to answer any questions about our products so do reach out to us with your queries.
For International Buyers: We are currently set up to ship within the EU and Canada. For all other countries please drop us a note and we will get back to you promptly with shipping rates and time.

Wonderful, prized early Schuco 2005 wind-up car with balloon toting mouse driver in original box.
Desirable soft jade green color, bright red seat. Gray mouse is likely steel (magnet sticks) covered in felt and holding a yellow and red hard plastic balloon. Product name: Curvy Board/Balance Board: Natural Finish with a Green Sunburst
Description:
The gift of the Curvy Board: WE bring an authentic Waldorf Inspired open-ended tool that has been handed down from generations of outside the box thinkers. We are dedicated to bringing the best quality materials, craftsmanship and love to each and every board, handmade within our own family, shared with yours. Your Child’s happiness is our goal just watches their faces. 
Each board can safely hold two grown adults each weighing 200lbs one either end while rocking back and forth like a seesaw.
The Curvy Board measures 34" in length, 12" in width, and 7" in height from floor to top of curve (when laying like a rainbow). 
Curvy boards are teeter totters, balance beams, slides, and... anything else your child can dream up. This unlimited range of possibilities is what makes open ended toy an ideal 
learning toy for 21st century learning skills. 
In a world where computers “know” all the facts, it is the imagination, innovation, and creativity of the human mind that has value. It is said that rocking helps develop a child’s sense of balance and for the brain to sort sensory impressions. The value in any toy is not what the toy can do, but what the child can do with it
If you ask to ask what it is, you know it's going to require some imagination. It'll send them outdoors, get their bodies moving and inspire their minds to start racing - and that's a lot more than you can say about most toys today.
Made from 9 layers of Maple Hardwood, sanded smooth, and finished with varnish. Each board is handmade so no two are alike, each board offers its unique design from nature. 
**Customers are strongly urged to exercise appropriate caution when using any items from Open Ended Creations. Children should be supervised during play. The purchaser assumes all responsibilities for any injuries resulting from the use of this item.**

Product name: Wooden farm animal toys - Wooden animal toys for kids - Wooden toy animals - Toy farm animals - Miniature animal toys - Easter gift
Description:
This listing is for a set of wooden animal toys for kids.  These wooden toy animals are small enough to be easy to hold and play with.  They are simple, unpainted farm animal toys.  Your child can have hours of imaginative fun with these 10 simple toy farm animals.  The largest, the horse, is about 4.75" tall and the smallest, the sheep, is about 2" tall.  They are made of pine and are unfinished.  Included are a horse, colt, cow, calf, billy goat, milk goat, dog, kitty, sheep, and pig.
The wooden animals are sanded and ready to play with.  My mom has been making these animals for decades now and selling them at craft shows in Oregon.  My kids played with them when they were little and had so much fun making animal noises.  You and you child can paint them if you want to make them unique to your family and to make a fun special memory.  There are no moving parts, no batteries required.  The only noise and action will be fueled by the imagination of your kids.  None of the animals fit completely inside the choke tester so they are great for kids of all ages.  That said, there is no better way to keep kids safe than adult supervision.  Have fun playing with you kids with these great animals.
These wooden farm animals with their fabric storage bag will make a great child's gift.  Your friends will appreciate that there are no beeps, bells or whistles.  Girls and boys alike love to play with animals.  With 10 animals to play with there are plenty to share with siblings and friends.
Included with the set is a colorful fabric storage bag.  The fabric used will vary depending on fabric availability, the bag show is an example, but may be of a different fabric than is currently available. The bag will hold all the animals and would make a great gift bag also.

Product name: Baby Receiving Blanket or Hospital Blanket Plush Bunny
Description:
If you are like me- the sentimental momma- you cannot bring yourself to stow away the adorable blanket that you wrapped your baby in when they were born; but at the same time, you don't know what to do with it.  Why not let me turn it into a lovely plush bunny rabbit for you or your kiddo?!!  Pull out that memory that's laying folded up in a box and send it my way!
I KNOW THIS IS A LOT BUT PLEASE READ EVERYTHING BELOW
Okay- bottom line basics:
You place your order, select if you want just the plain bunny or add pink or blue embroidery. Once your order goes through I email you with information and the PO Box address. You mail me your blanket. I make a bunny and then mail it back. Simple as that :)
Here's the details:
So, whether it is the traditional hospital blanket or other well loved receiving blanket, I can turn it into an adorable keepsake. (Please note: The bunny pictured is an example that I made from my son's blanket. I do not provide the blanket for you, you will mail your blanket to me.)
I offer your child's name and birth date embroidered onto the bottom of the feet in a matching thread color (please select blue or pink) for an additional 10.    👉🏻👉🏻Please include in the "Notes to Seller" or Convo me the Name and Date you wish to be embroidered.👈🏻👈🏻   (I usually try to match the shade of blue or pink that's in your blanket unless otherwise requested).   I use premium polyester fiber fill to stuff your bunny with and embroidery floss for the nose and eyes.  Sitting down its about 11" tall. The overall length (with the legs stretched out) is about 15" tall. Width at its widest is about 6". 
Once I receive your order, I will email you an instruction page with all the information you'll need to mail me your blanket. Please only send ONE blanket per bunny.  Current turn-around time is about 4 weeks. 
Standard hospital receiving blankets are usually appx. 25"x"30- please make sure your blanket is not much smaller.  If you're not sure feel free to email or convo me. 
Thin flannel receiving blankets are the best for bunny quality but if you have questions on your fabric please feel free to convo or email me.
While I do not offer gift certificates for my shop specifically, I do accept Etsy gift cards which you can purchase and then can be used in my shop. I can also email you a nice page that you can print out that has my shop name and information to give with your Etsy gift card. 
PLEASE NOTE: If you're buying this to gift to someone else please make sure that they're ready to mail me their blanket within 1 week of the order date. Etsy has a limited time allotted for me to ship the item so I need to be able to get the bunnies completed within that time frame. For gifting, the best thing to do is give an Etsy gift certificate along with my shop information. 
*DISCLAIMER ON MUSLIN BLANKET: The “muslin” blankets are very popular right now but their lightweight and slightly stretchy nature make them a difficult material to work with.  I can make bunnies from blankets like the Aden and Anais wraps but please PLEASE note the following before choosing this fabric:  the thin fabric does not hold its shape as well as the flannel so be aware that your bunny may not hold up as long.  Please do NOT send me “cotton gauze”- this is not the same as the swaddle blankets like Aden and Anais; it is much more stretchy and far thinner (I purchased some from a fabric store and learnt this the hard way).

Product name: Dragon-themed Luxury Children's Playhouse
Description:
My other company is called Magical Playhouses (www.magicalplayhouses.com). I design, build, and deliver luxury playhouses for children all over the western United States.
Make childhood magical again! Can you imagine growing up with memories of playing in this? 
This playhouse was featured at the 2015 Bellevue ArtsFair and in the current (August 2016) issue of Fine Homebuilding.  It took 600 hours to build, with 150 of those in the carving alone. Material costs were close to 7k, so this playhouse is priced at 29,995, though I'm open to reasonable offers.  
Most of the playhouses I build for clients are more in the 5-10k range, but I built this as an example to showcase my abilities. That being said I would be estatic if there was a child out there who might grow up with happy memories of their dragon pkayhouse.
Now, if you worry about your children or grandchildren aging out of a luxury playhouse too quickly, I also offer a 3-year lease option to greater Puget Sound residents at 450/month, and after that period is up, you can continue month to month. We can also do lease-to-own and owner financing, if that would be more appealing. There's obviously some fine print to these options, so send me a message if you're curious and I'll send you more information. 
The Dragon is built and waiting for that special child who, like mine, is obsessed with dragons. This playhouse measures 6'8" wide, 12'6" tall and 10' long. It is just about as large as I can pull down the highway without moving lines, and in fact, the head is designed to be removed for this purpose.
It weighs approximately 3,000 pounds and, just like a hot tub, it can easily be craned into any backyard.
For more pictures, please visit: http://www.magicalplayhouses.com/for-sale/ 
If you are a reader of Fine Homebuilding, this playhouse will be featured in the September 2016 issue, due out in mid-July. Keep an eye out for it!
Depending on your location, and method of installation, this playhouse can be in your yard in as soon as one week. 
Features:
- Hand-carved cedar dragon heads and tail
- Insulated 2x4 walls. Broan wall heater (wired with a safety shut-off switch 52" off the floor).
- Double-paned tempered glass windows.
- 1 3/4" solid ash arch top door with figured maple panels and replica of the sword 'Sting' from Lord of the Rings.
- Stained glass windows
- Built in window seat with pull-out step for the little ones, cabinetry with soft-close hinges. and professionally upholstered 4" cushions.
- Hidden compartment in the floor.
- Bookshelf with numerous dragon-themed children's books and stuffed animals.
- Built in chalkboard cabinet with soft-close hinges, featuring walnut shelves for holding chalk.
- No. 1 western red cedar sidewall shingles and roof shakes.
- Pine tongue and groove interior walls.
- Copper light fixtures.
- Benjamin Moore paints
Please don't hesitate to ask me any questions, including requests for new commissions,
Chris

Product name: Waldorf Calendar - Waldorf Steiner  Waldorf inspired education - Rainbow Gnome COLOUR DAY Days Of The Week Calendar FREE Shipping Australia
Description:
Waldorf inspired education tool
✿ Waldorf COLOUR DAY OF THE WEEK Calendar ✿
✫ This handcrafted Waldorf Calendar is my top #1 best selling item of all time! ✫ 
                 ✫.•°*”˜˜”*°•.✫ THANK YOU! ✫.•°*”˜˜”*°•.✫ 
As most parents & educators would agree, young children are Sensory Beings. Our children relate to the world through their senses: the sense of sight, touch, sound and so on.
Learning the days of the week using colour therefore resonates with younger children in a more gentle and intuitive way than using numbers or names to represent each day. 
HOW IT WORKS:-
(See video here:: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uO9dZJ62OoQ )
   A wonderful way to start your child's day! ::
Each gnome is the COLOUR of a day of the week, as suggested by R. Steiner. Purple is Monday, Red is Tuesday... and so follows. As the week progresses, the gnome of the day sits up on his little stage, announcing his colour ALL day.
(See my blog post for more info - http://www.hinterlandmama.com/2013/06/colour-days-of-week-waldorf-children.html)
* Original and Unique Hinterland Mama design 
* Ideal Weekly Rhythm teaching tool
* Waldorf Inspired and used in many ELC and family settings
-------------------
To make your gnome calendar into the unique, handmade treasure that will become an heirloom in your family, I personally cut a piece of beautifully scented local Camphor Laurel timber into a pod-shaped base and then carefully sand it FIVE times by hand to achieve a silky finish. 
I then hand-rub the wooden base with my own natural grapeseed/beeswax polish to seal the wood and protect it from potential stains and moisture. 
Each peg doll is gently sanded in a similar manner to match the smooth texture of the wooden base. 
The next step is to gather my teensiest paint brushes and well-worn Lyra watercolour paintbox. I lovingly handpaint each charming little gnome with his own individually coloured tunic.
The hewn holes in the wooden base are painted now, too, with the same delicious watercolours to match the gnomes' tunics, with one colour for each day of the week. The holes are then lovingly waxed and polished, as are the little gnomes, one at a time.
I then get out my sewing basket and, with the precision of the fabled shoemaker's elves, I cut tiny hats from my collection of exquisite quality, European felt fabrics. I lovingly stitch together the tiny pieces to form classicly pointed gnome hats to match the colourful  tunics.
I dress each little wooden peg gnome in his own felt cap, using natural, non-toxic glue to secure the felt to the wood in a seamless manner so that curious little fingers will be able to handle the peg gnomes without the adornment coming loose and detaching. 
Of course, as individually handcrafted items made of small parts, these peg dolls are not designed to be used as toys for toddlers. The best and safest use is for children ages 4 and up, so please use care to protect both your children and the gnome set from harm or damage.
  if you like my Gnome Calendars, please Favourite this item by clicking the ♥ Heart ♥ at the top! <
*Dimensions~
Base:: approx. 18cm width x 11cm depth x 2cm height
Gnomes:: approx. 6.5cm height (to top of hat) x 1.5cm base
🌸 I use all Natural and Sustainable materials 🌸
Included: a wooden base and 7 gnomes in a rainbow of colours
~The wood used is Camphor Laurel, a beautiful timber with a rich, varied colour grain throughout. The wood is sustainably cut and processed locally to my home.

Product name: Custom Trophys Made to Order
Description:
Made to order custom trophies is a new offering that we are going to try.  The examples shown were a custom order from a company for unique trophies to be presented to the winners of their annual 'Texas Hold em' poker contest and their annual 'Mardi Gras Cook Off'.
As you can see in the photos, I have pictures that show our signature technique of copper coloring metal and applying a glossy powder coated finish.  This is the same technique we use on most of our products, unless we are powder coating with a color.
The 'Texas Hold em' is 15" wide and 15" tall.  The Cook Off trophy is 15" x 20".  Both have been cut from 16 gauge metal and ground down to make the metal shiny silver.  The metal is then treated with an additive to bring about the copper tones, then treated with another additive to give it the burnished tones.  Notice the pattern from the grinding showing through the color.  Then the piece is powder coated with a clear protective coating.  It almost looks like it has a 3 dimensional depth and It changes as the light hits it from different angles.  These make beautiful gifts, too.  
So, if you have an interest in a custom trophy for an occasion or a special person, click on 'Request a Custom Order' I need is your thoughts on the matter and I will put something together for you to approve.  Once we agree, I will create it and post it RESERVED for you.
The price will depend on your design, the lettering, images, etc., and of course the size of the finished product. We charge by the inches cut.  I don't like to go much smaller in size because letters get too close and the heat of my cutting torch has a tendency to warp the lettering. When designing a whole new trophy there is a one time, 25.00 design fee. If you order again and use the Sam design there will not be a new design fee charged since it is in our system.
For a reference point, the Texas trophy sold for 55 and the Cookoff went for 50.  The shipping will probably be in the 15 to 17 range, depending on where I ship it to.  The postage is based on size and weight, and where the package is being sent.  When you type your request in be sure to add your address and zip code.  
Etsy requires us to put in a price, here in this listing. Since I don't know the final price, because I don't know what you want, I am putting in the base price of the Texas Hold em at 55 and shipping at 15.  You may want one of the trophies, as is, with just a change in the company name or no name at all.  The price will not change for that.  If you like to have card parties or have a recreation room with a card table, this is just the piece you want on the wall to let your challengers know that you are a serious card player.  Let me know what you are wanting.  After, we send you a digital design of what you have told us and a price quote, you can approve it, cancel it, or keep on working on it.
Please convo me with questions and we can start having communications toward a very unique gift or presentation that you will not find in any stores.
Overview:
Handmade item

Product name: Tabletop MAME Arcade Enclosure Kit for Raspberry Pi System
Description:
Are you interested in more than 2 players?  Check out our new modular design here:  
https://www.etsy.com/listing/490009769/2-4-player-modular-mame-arcade-console
This is a kit of unfinished wooden parts for a tabletop MAME cabinet using Raspberry Pi.  Get the TRUE arcade feel while you play all the classics on this compact emulator console.
..or go here for the new single player version!  
https://www.etsy.com/listing/264441384/single-player-arcade-console-for?ref=listing-shop-header-0
Currently available in a beautiful 4.5mm Birch plywood, with a fabulous surface and a very lovely grain. 
I built the first one of these just to do something with an unused Raspberry Pi, and everyone who played it loved it!  After that, I cleaned it up and made a bunch of improvements to the final version you see here.  
This is an open source project - so if you want to cut one of your own, go for it - the free (but non-commercial) plans are available on Thingiverse here:  http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:675143     
This listing is for those who don't have the time or resources to make their own, or..  who want to support me, the designer. (thanks!)  
Assembly instructions, and a description of the process are on instructables here.
http://www.instructables.com/id/Tabletop-Arcade-Mame-Box-for-Raspberry-Pi/
This kit contains only the wooden parts, you will need to supply the guts.  In the completed picture above, the kit is shown assembled with
Raspberry Pi model B running the free PiPlay software
eBay "60-in-1" Dual Joystick/Button combination (including XinMo USB interface)
USB and HDMI cords, and little rubber feet for the corners.
A bit of wood glue.
The gentle angle mimics a real arcade experience on any countertop or table, and the reinforced ribs inside the box create a very sturdy and durable play surface.  It's made from Baltic Birch, and looks beautiful in natural colors or stained.
The box is shown with a normal 20-button layout, with the joystick and 6 player buttons using the standard "sega1" layout from slagcoin.  Drop me a line to inquire about a different layout or different number of buttons.  Most layouts are easily workable, as long as there is room for the guts and wiring harnesses.
Assembly takes about an hour using standard wood glue, and installation/wiring of the electronics takes another hour.  It's all quite easy, and can be completed in an evening or two or a Saturday.
The shipping weight is about 3lb, and your parts will be shipped as soon as they are cut!  As with any laser-cut item - it smells like burnt wood!  Give it a couple days in the garage to air out, or trust that any stain or sealer will kill the smell completely.

Product name: Witcher 3 Gwent Card Playing Surface Mat -  Cotton Sateen Cloth
Description:
Do you love Witcher 3?
Do you love Gwent?
Do you own the cards but have nothing to play them on?
That was my situation and I couldn't find a suitable playing surface anywhere, so I decided to do something about it and create my very own unique playing surface! It became so popular amongst my Gwent-playing friends that I thought I'd make it available to all Gwent fans via Etsy!
I have also added a new PREMIUM version of my Gwent mat which I have made out of a high quality Neoprene 1000gsm material and fabric surface. It basically resembles a giant mouse mat (ie. cloth top, black foam rubber underneath). This makes for an excellent playing surface which doesn't require ironing, has wonderful grip on the table top, and can be easily rolled up once you are finished. This new mat can be found in my shop.
Playing mat features:
- Allows you to play your very own real-life games of Gwent (assuming of course you own the card decks already).
- The scale of the playing surface perfectly matches the official Gwent game cards.
- The play area is printed on a high quality Cotton Sateen cloth, the edges of which are folded and hemmed by hand to prevent fraying.
- Once you're done playing you can easily fold it away making it a very portable item.
- Being cloth, it's also more resilient than a paper/cardboard equivalent.
- The mat measures approx. 84.5cm x 76.5cm.
At the moment I am making these to order so there is a delivery time of 10-12 days. Trust me though, if you are a Gwent fan and already own the card decks, this mat is worth the wait! I'm also happy to post anywhere in Europe and in the US and Canada - although this might add a few days to the delivery time.
If you have any questions, please don't hesistate to ask! :)
PLEASE NOTE: THIS AUCTION IS JUST FOR THE CLOTH PLAYING MAT. ALL CARDS AND OTHER ACCESSORIES SEEN IN THE PHOTOS ARE NOT INCLUDED! YOU WILL NEED AT LEAST TWO GWENT CARD DECKS TO PLAY THE GAME ON THIS MAT.

Product name: Medieval Playing Cards Renaissance Deck of Cards Historical Whimsical Unique Blue Playing Cards Blue Deck of Cards Designer Playing Cards
Description:
Medieval Playing Cards Renaissance Deck of Cards Historical Whimsical Unique Blue Playing Cards Blue Deck of Cards Designer Playing Cards
----------------------------------------------------
Playing cards were invented in Imperial China, and likely spread through Asia into Europe via the Silk Road. When cards first appeared in Europe in the 14th century, they were designed to represent European royalty and nobility. 
The figures in the face cards of this deck are inspired by real people who ruled Europe in the late medieval period. You can see all the face cards in the second image of this listing. They are as follows:
❖ Clubs Suit: 
- King: Christian II of Denmark
- Queen: Isabella of Austria 
- Jack: Norwegian pirate Elise Eskilsdotter
❖ Diamonds Suit: 
- King: Holy Roman Emperor Maximilian I
- Queen: Mary Duchess of Burgundy
- Jack: Dutch philosopher Erasmus
❖ Hearts Suit: 
- King: Florentine ruler Giuliano de'Medici
- Queen: Guiliano's lover (and model for Botticelli's "Birth of Venus"), Simonetta Vespucci 
- Jack: Renaissance artist Sandro Botticelli
❖ Spades Suit: 
- King: Louis XII of France
- Queen: Mary Tudor
- Jack: French vigilante Jeanne Hachette
----------------------------------------------------
Specifics:
❖ All cards, front and back, were designed by me, Laura Inksetter
❖ 54 standard bridge-sized playing cards (including 2 joker cards)
❖ Card dimensions: 2.25 x 3.5 inches (56mm x 88mm)
❖ Printed on 270gsm cardstock with a very light glossy finish
❖ Each card back features a unique rabbit design
❖ Each deck comes in a white tuck box with my rabbit design on the front
❖ Ships in a protective bubble mailer

Product name: Marble Roller
Description:
This wooden marble roller is fun for the young and the young at heart! Don't be surprised if you find it hard to tear yourself away! 
Fill the top rail with marbles, drop one marble in the front of the line of marbles to get the roller started. The weight of the marble will drop the lever, hitting the pin and releasing the next marble in the line-up. The process continues until  all of the marbles have circulated through. 
Handcrafted in NC from poplar, the marble roller includes 15 marbles, and the box for collecting the marbles as they exit at the end of the run. 
21"x 16"x 7"

Product name: Theremin - Electronic Instrument - GENUINE True Analog Theremin Theramin Thermin
Description:
The world’s first electronic instrument!
Most people associate the other-worldly sound of a theremin with vintage science fiction / horror movies, or bands such as Man or Astro Man that utilized the instrument in their musical mix. Invented in the 1920's (it is widely considered to be the world's first synthesizer) the theremin still seems futuristic today and is used in commercial audio & films as well. This electronic instrument is a bit unusual in that it is played by moving your hand near the antenna without actually coming in contact with the theremin itself.
************************************
This listing is for one completely assembled "plug and play" Theremaniacs Theremin! Theremin plugs into an amplifier with a standard 1/4 inch guitar cord. It will sit quietly until your hand is about three feet away. As your hand comes nearer to the antenna, the pitch gradually becomes higher until it is inaudible. Covers 7 octaves - from soaring high notes through great growling lows. 
Theremin is powered by a quality 9 volt alkaline (included). AC adapters will add hum and instability so we only use pure DC battery power! . One alkaline battery will last about 500 hours (several years of average use) and is easy to replace. The sound does not suffer as battery power is consumed during use. Draws only 1 milliamp, far less than ordinary effects pedal. Set it up anywhere you want! 
Theremin is assembled from common components without the use of esoteric parts that may be unobtainable in the future. We do not sand off part numbers! Some manufacturers will hide the component values they use by obliterating the markings making future repairs impossible! 
All high quality components and construction featuring a laser etched professional quality circuit board with genuine Inductor Coils in a classic Dual Oscillator Heterodyne design - Real Theremin sound and playability! 
Changeable output sound from mellow to coarse. 
Variable operating frequency and external sensitivity control. 
************************************
Only THEREMANIACS GENUINE THEREMINS are guaranteed for parts and workmanship for as long as you own the instrument! 
PRODUCT OPTION AVAILABLE! You can choose from: Screw thread Microphone Stand Mounting, or rubber foot table top style! 
METAL thread microphone stand mounting will fit ALL mic stands. (Sorry, stand not included!) 
************************************
A wiggling motion of the hand produces a vibrato effect. 
Input to a reverb, echo unit, flanger, or others will create wild effects! 
Run this through an effects rack and you will be amazed at your sonic creations! 
Thousands of Happy Customers World Wide! 
Your Satisfaction Is Assured! 
Please email if you have any questions chuckcollins(at)prodigy.net
************************************
Theremaniacs Theremins ~ Available World-Wide since 1993! 
My product was featured at the 1997 International Theremin Festival and in 
'Electronic Musician' Magazine 
(December 1999 - as one of 29 great gift ideas!) 
Used by people across the globe 
including the band 
'Smashmouth' on 'The Tonight Show'! (6-13-00) 
Over 1000 uses from Music to Noise!
We have sold to individuals from all over the world for house party to recording studio use, many schools including schools for the blind & special needs children (used in theater and band). 
Only ANALOG Theremins give you the BEST Sound Around!

Product name: zine - "Not Straight Not White Not Male" - 3rd edition
Description:
Price jumped because I no longer have access to free printing! I apologize if this makes my zine inaccessible to anyone. If you have concerns, please don't hesitate to send me a message and we'll figure out a way to get you a zine.
*4 YEARS LATER* I have ups and downs with how I feel about this zine. It’s been over four years of evolving and growing that makes me feel very embarrassed about the writing compiled in this zine. There have been many times when I’ve hovered over the “Delete Listing” button on Etsy, but every time I contemplate this, I get a new message from someone who says my writing made them laugh and scream and cry and feel not alone and see everything differently. They remind me that just because I feel that I am past that particular revelatory identity-forming stage of my life does not mean that there aren’t others who need to keep hearing the thoughts and emotions that poured out of me so necessarily 4 years ago. In summary, this writing was crucial to my sanity and existence in 2012, but it is now 2016. It no longer feels all-encompassingly representative of the politics of my identity, but I deeply understand it’s significance for some people who have not yet heard or articulated the things I wrote about. I intend to distribute this zine as long as there are people who need it. At the same time, I am thinking about a second zine titled “Not Straight Not White.. Boy Though?”
____________________________________
I am second generation Vietnamese-American, female/boy and v v gay. Written mid & post being violently dragged through white punk communities.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
INTRO NOTE:
“I wrote this zine because there is a lack of media that I can really, truly relate to. It is glaringly obvious that this radical scene is comprised mostly of heteros, of whites, and of males. I am Asian, I am hella gay, and I am female.
Disclaimer: I wrote this for me a lot more than I wrote it for you. There is a lack of solution offering, and at the same time a lot rambling, because it is cathartic for me. It is highly anecdotal; I write from experience. Don’t assume that my aim is to educate ignorant fucks. It is not my job to cry and bleed so that they can fucking evolve.
Always for the greater gay,
xROSIx”
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
CONTENTS:
Hand-designed cover
Introduction note
“And Ode to Chinkophiles: Y.e.l.l.o.w.F.e.v.e.r”
"Chauncey: This fucking guy" - a detailed account of the wildly inappropriate escapades of a middle-aged white man projecting his yellow fetish onto yours truly
“I Have Discovered the Words with Which to Express my Visceral Resentment of White Cockiness” - where I bitterly examine my aesthetic inferiority complex
(^ and a follow-up clarification on the preceding essay)
“Sorry, Mom” - being vietnamese-american in america can be fucking irritating..
“Pre-Gay” - some things i want to say to old friends and family
“But Really, Come On, You Surely Know By Now” - about the differences in expectations in ‘female’ attire and aesthetic and ‘male’ attire and aesthetic
"Dysfunction Over Fashion" - how my boi-complex fucks with my wardrobe choices
“Proving Myself: as an Asian and as a Female” - where I discuss, shortly, my relentless need to prove to everyone that I can be “better” than my stereotype
(^ and a follow-up clarification on the preceding essay)
“Your Masculinity is Under Attack: In response to the new onslaught of ad campaigns that perpetuate sexism under the guise of ‘making fun of sexism through exaggeration’” - an obnoxious, satirical piece
“Some Shit Some M-Fuckers Said to Me" documentation of vocalized, 21st century gendered bigotry, just a few months’ worth of sexist, patronizing remarks
“Some More Shit Some Other M-Fuckers Said to Me" - casual list of some racist shit people have said to me
“Not Asian Enough / Too Asian: month one - working in a Vietnamese restaurant couched in white O.C.”
"Broken" - a weird arty thing symbolizing South East Asian-American diasporic identity crises idk
“E.S.L.” - short and dry. about my being a 1st generation American in my family and not understanding American customs
“A/S/L? 13/M/CA” - a short essay about how i used to create online role-playing characters to live out my dreams and escape my identity
"Don't Tell Your Parents I Think They're Racist: (unless I've asked you to)" - PSA to white allies. In summary, don't decide for me when I should have race talks/race fights, and don't decide for me which relationships I must now compromise for the "greater good"
(^ a follow-up/amendment on the preceding essay where, upon further analysis of white-privilege and anti-blackness, i retract some contentions i'd previously made)
“White People Making White People Jokes” - where i discuss why i don’t think it’s always appropriate
"Sup, Hypocrites" - shortly addressing skinny-shame, prude-shame, and femme-shame
"Microcosms of Patriarchy" - hiding from the world in the radical scene does not mean hiding from non-consensual, intimate contact, unfortunately
"Being Conscious of Womanhood" - an analysis of the unconscious things i do because i am hyper-aware of what it means to be a woman in this society
"On Privilege, Allies, and Bitterness" - me listing and rambling for a page about the aforementioned topics
“Cathartic Vomit” - me being pissed about this and that
comic relief

PROVIDING THE CORRECT RING SIZE IS VERY IMPORTANT - PLEASE READ
Providing the Correct Ring Size:
When placing your order, please make sure you provide the correct ring size. If you do not know your ring size, or want to double check, it is advisable to visit a local jeweler. Many jewelers will measure your finger for free. 
Tips for accurate measurement:
• Measure your finger in warm temperatures at the end of the day (this is when your finger is at its largest).
• Avoid measuring cold fingers (cold fingers are smaller than warm fingers).
• If your knuckle is much larger than the base of your finger, make sure and measure both the base of your finger as well as your knuckle and select a size between the two to allow enough room to comfortably slip over your knuckle.
• For wide rings (more than 6mm), select one size larger than what your actual ring size is.
Please note that your primary hand’s ring size can be a half to a full size larger.
Please do not use any printable sizers that can be found online. Most of these are inaccurate.

Product name: Artist's book, Joseph Cornell, coptic stitched book,stocking gift,  hand bound book, art gift,  Book Art
Description:
This artist's book is handmade, digitally printed artwork which would make a wonderful gift.   It features work inspired by and referencing Joseph Cornell's assemblage work, of which he was a pioneer during the 1930's in New York.  He was self taught, and a deeply poetic man, collecting ephemera and curating them to narrate the world around him, and the world within.  His younger brother died young of cerebral palsy and Joseph had deep love for him, having been his carer. He was interested in the surreal artists, and influenced heavily in his life by Christian Science, and I have referenced this in the book.  He also was a great believer in beauty, and believed that artists renew and transform materials, experiences, and ideas, and this belief fueled his ability to communicate the beauty and magic in ordinary, often forgotten things. 
 Enclosed in the book is a postcard I have designed and written a message to Joseph Cornell which goes some way to explaining his influence on me.
  
As each book is individually made , the cover may be slightly different to the one pictured, but will be just as beautiful!  If you have any preferences or special requirements for dedications, please contact me, and I will try to satisfy them!
Every book I make is researched and completed by myself , reflecting my interests in history, art, literature, philosophy and nature.  
The leaves are digitally printed on heavyweight double coated watercolour paper ( 190g.s.m Bockingford) for excellent print quality and longevity.

Product name: Ballads and Sonnets by Dante Gabriel Rossetti / 1882, Ellis and White, London / Last Volume of Work Published in Rossetti's Lifetime
Description:
"But the song's end was all of his love; 
And well his heart was grac'd
With her smiling lips and tear-bright eyes
As his arm went round her waist."
Dante Gabriel Rossetti was an English poet, illustrator, painter and translator. He founded the Pre-Raphaelite Brotherhood in 1848 with William Holman Hunt and John Everett Millais. Rossetti was later to be the main inspiration for a second generation of artists and writers influenced by the movement, most notably William Morris and Edward Burne-Jones. His work also influenced the European Symbolists and was a major precursor of the Aesthetic movement.
I have uncovered here an extremely early copy of Rossetti's "Ballads and Sonnets". Originally published in 1881 by Ellis and White of Bond Street, London. It was the last volume to be published in Rossetti's lifetime. Here is a fourth edition from a year later by the same publishing house in 1882, the year of his death. Some of this poetry was originally buried with his wife Elizabeth Siddal; however, years after her death he exhumed her grave to recover them and went on to publish them in 1870. Ballads and Sonnets contain some of this and later works.
Rossetti's early poetry was influenced by John Keats. His later poetry was characterised by the complex interlinking of thought and feeling, especially in his sonnet sequence, The House of Life (included in this volume). Also included are the ballads Rose Mary; The White Ship and The King's Tragedy, Lyrics &c. and a number of sonnets influenced by paintings.
In good condition for an antique title and quite beautifully designed as would be expected, this is a lovely book. The pages have some tanning around the edges and are rough cut on the sides. There is a neatly inked name on an inside front plain endpaper, otherwise no other writing, marks or inscriptions. There is tanning to the endpapers and to a couple of the pages in the middle of the book, otherwise clean and tightly bound. The blue decorative endpapers have a charming floral design by Rossetti (see photos).
The dark green cloth boards have a gilt trellis and flower pattern to all sides. The boards have picked up some rubbing around the edges and in particular to the corners where there is some rubbing away of the cloth. They have picked up the odd mark, but overall remain strikingly attractive with the gilt pattern remaining very good and bright. The spine also has some rubbing and rolling to the cloth at the top and bottom, but otherwise is un-faded and again the gilt ornamentation has lasted well here. Mildly cracked hinges mean slightly wobbly boards, but this in no way affects the book block and the binding remains good and tight.
A beautiful Victorian collection, "Ballads and Sonnets" will be wrapped with care in tissue and ribbon.
H 20cm X W 14cm, 337 pages. I dispatch worldwide daily from the UK. Further shipping information can be found in the shop policies section if required.

Product name: Antique Parasol Cover Net Lace White Fully Restored Excellent Condition
Description:
This parasol cover was quite dingy and dirty when I found it. I gently soaked it to remove all signs of age, ironed and lightly spray starched,  and it turned out perfect! There are no stains, it's pure white. There's just a tiny 1/4" hole in the netting near the top but it's under the top lace layer so it doesn't show. And the outer lace edging has a few holes and one 6" section where it's frayed and weak. 
It's really hard to find these parasol covers. I guess they were so delicate not many survived.
Please note: there are no loops to attach this to the outer edge of a parasol, just the center hole.
This is 20" from top to bottom, 40" diameter.

All our gowns are designed to feel lightweight and easy-to wear, be comfortable and grant you freedom of movement. To achieve that, we select only high-quality fabrics: soft, nice to skin and well fitting. All materials are reasonably wrinkle-resistant.
Order processing:
Our dresses are hand-made and manually decorated in our studio according to your order. Standard production time is 4 weeks. We ship internationally via EMS Express postal service; other options (UPS, DHL, FedEx etc.) are available at buyer's request. Shipping usually takes 5-10 days depending on destination.
Rush orders:
Please contact us if your situation requires shorter production times; we will do our best to help you.
Sizing:
To ensure best fit, we will make your dress especially for you. After your order we will contact you and send the list of measurements we need for this model, along with instructions on how to take them. We design all our models to be easy-fitting, so generally - no further alterations will be required.
Length:
Generally we recommend adjusting the length on-site. In this case you will not be limited in selecting your wedding shoes or heels and choosing the most comfortable length. With our dresses length adjustment is a very simple procedure which can be done by any local tailor, or by a handy non-professional.
If you would rather prefer us to make the dress to your height - please let us know, we will happily do it for you.
Should you have any other questions, please feel free to contact us for assistance!

Please measure yourself
*clothing is make for order.You may pick a size from the standard sizes below.
Bust: ________
Waist: ________

Waist to hem length:_________(ask for knee length dress)
Hollow to floor: ______________(ask for floor length dress)
Your Height (in bare feet): _______
Heels:_______
For How-to-Measure:
Bust
▲This is not your bra size
▲Wear a no padded bra(your dress will have a built-in bra)
▲Relax arms at sides
▲Pull tape across the fullest part of the bust
Waist
▲Find the natural waist
▲This is the smallest part of the waist
▲Usually about 1 in. above belly button
▲Keep tape slightly loose to allow for breathing room
Hips
▲Find the widest part of the hips
▲Usually about 7 in. below natural waist
▲Tape should brush across both hipbones
Waist to Hemline
▲Begin at Waist(usually about 1 in. above belly button)
▲Pull tape straight down to Where you want the hem is
For example, if you want the dress knee-length, then measure from Waist to your Knee.
If you want the dress ends at 3 in. above the knee(let's name it point A), then measure from Waist to A.
Hollow to Floor
▲Stand straight with feet together 
▲Measure in BARE FEET
▲Begin at the hollow space between the collarbones and pull tape straight down to the floor
▲To fit high heels, I’ll add an extra 5 cm onto custom-sized floor-length dresses and dresses with trains.(If you have special requirement, like you'll wear 10 cm heels, please let me know.)

Description:
3 x 100g skeins of beautiful and soft luxury hand dyed yarn. Half of each skein is hand dyed with a vibrant rainbow, the other half a solid colour; jet black, stormy grey and pure undyed white. 
Available in Sock weight - 400m / DK weight 225m / Aran/Worsted weight -166m
All of my colourways are available on sock/ fingering, DK weight and Aran / Worsted. On either 100% Superwash Merino or upgrade to my  luxury merino/nylon/cashmere blend.
I offer a caking service, so if you'd like your yarn balled for just £1 each simply go to the listing and add it to your basket!
I pride myself on sourcing locally. The bare wool and all my dyes are from a British supplier. 
Washing tips: Machine wash on a delicate cycle and lay flat to dry. Hand washing is always recommended. Wash separately, or with similar colors.
All of my yarns go through a 4 stage wash treatment before shipping however it is possible that there will be a small amount of colour bleeding on the first couple of washes, this is normal and shouldn't change the colour of the yarn.
Whilst I have tried to accurately represent the colours on the listing, all skeins are unique and colour may vary slightly on different monitors.  
Don't forget to check out my other listings! If you can't see something you're looking for then please pop me a message, I can do full custom bespoke orders, just let me know what you love!

Product name: Weaving Loom Kit - Weaving frame, shed stick, yarn needle, weaving warp and yarn
Description:
INSTRUCTIONS to use this loom are free on my YouTube channel WEAVEWITHPAT 
Our weaving kit has been put together with much thought to ensure you get a good start on your weaving journey. 
The hardwood weaving loom frame has been designed and hand made by me and my artist partner Martin Hodge. Its construction allows for flexibility in the warp sett (the space allowance between each warp thread) - essential to obtaining an even surface in your tapestry weaving projects. 
The kit comes with everything you need to start weaving, including an exclusive selection of three optional colorways from the Marta's Yarns collection of yarns. 
For those of you new to weaving, I have developed a series of free weaving lessons for beginners at my YouTube channel weavewithpat.  
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyr9Fd6kLZ8cDUYAX24jdTQ
The kit includes:
1 x handmade Australian hardwood weaving loom frame 34.5 cm x 42 cm (13.5" x 16.5").
1 x timber Shed Stick (weaving sword)
2 x timber yarn needles
- Enough high quality Swedish cotton weaving warp for one weaving. (Linen warp in an oatmeal color is also available - please convo me if you prefer the linen warp). 
- Enough yarn in one of three colorways - Brights, Naturals or Tonals - to complete your first weaving.
Happy weaving!
Pat xx
PS These looms are hand made to order so please allow 1 to 2 weeks for dispatch.

Product name: Medium * Modern Acrylic Lap Loom
Description:
MODERN. FUNCTIONAL. DURABLE. 
Approximately 7.75inches wide by 12.5 inches tall
This modern acrylic lap loom is laser cut by me, from a lovely clear acrylic that is approximately 1/4 inch thick for ultimate durability. The loom was designed to be portable, but also simple and beautiful in order to better show off your weaving work! Unlike wooden looms which have a more difficult time surviving extreme hot and cold temperatures, the acrylic loom withstands temperature fluctuations, and is not susceptible to humidity like bamboo and other softwoods.
The loom fits easily into a purse or tote-bag, making it a great size to take along to work, vacation, or the coffee shop! Order it with a comb and needle as a set and you're off to creating your first piece of woven wall art. A great gift for a friend or loved one who enjoys crafts and fiber arts.
Medium:
7.75inches x 12.5inches

Customer satisfaction is my highest priority! Returns are determined on a case by case basis. All items are insured, so please contact seller immediately if your loom was damaged upon arrival.  USPS will be properly scolded for the error! : )
Wipe clean with a damp cloth. Do not bend. Store standing up when possible. Keep away from small children.

Product name: Greener Shades Dye
Description:
Greener Shades Dyes are a safe, non-hazardous, non-chrome dye for use on wool, silk, nylon or any animal fiber, formulated without using hazardous metals. Greener Shades dyes provide the wash- and light-fastness of traditional acid dyes without using metal compounds to achieve bright, beautiful colors.
Dying is the perfect way to get just the color you want for your yarn, fabric or finished products. Some ideas include a knitted scarf in your favorite color, a quilt in rainbow shades, or a tie-died t-shirt. You can also dye wood for an exciting, colorful project. The simplicity and ease of these dyes make it perfect for both beginners and professionals.
Each 1/2 ounce jar of dye is able to dye 3 lbs. of fiber at 1% Depth of Shade which produces brilliant color. Lesser amounts and color combinations can be used to achieve many thousands of colors, tints and shades.
Available colors are:
- Amazon Green
- Amethyst Purple
- Coral Reef Aqua
- Flame Red
- Midnight Black
- River Blue
- Ruby Red
- Sunset Orange
- Sunshine Yellow
Citric acid is used as a dye fixative and is safe, easy to measure and not messy or smelly.
The color sample/instruction card has yarn samples in all nine colors on one side and instructions for both simple and detailed dying for all kinds of fibers and fabrics on the back.
Purchase options include:
- A complete starter set with all nine colors in individual 1/2 oz. jars, an 8 oz. packet of citric acid and a color sample/instruction card priced at 45.00
- A set of all nine colors in individual 1/2 oz. jars priced at 40.00
- Individual colors in 1/2 oz. jars for 5.00 each
- An instruction card with dyed yarn samples priced at 3.50
If you order more than one jar of a single color, the amounts can be combined into one jar to save on shipping. Please contact us if you would like to use this option.
We will combine packing if possible with these or any other purchased items to save shipping costs for you.

VERSATILE: 
Move from heavy to fine wire with the same pair of Wubbers. You won't feel the need to switch pliers when you move from task to task.
PRECISION: 
The unique Wubbers finish holds tight without marring your metal. There is a fine line between metal jaws with a finish that is matte enough to hold tight, but also smooth enough to help prevent marring. Wubbers are the best in successfully finding that balance.
PRACTICAL: 
Wubbers consistently outperform pliers that cost twice as much.
GENTLE: 
The amazing Wubbers handles won't leave your hands feeling 20 years older. The padded grips provide extra comfort and feel nice in your hands. The smooth-action springs help prevent fatigue while the sleek shape of the handles makes them easy to grip.

Product name: 10 Drilled (5/32" Hole) Medium Deer Antler Tines.  Perfect for crafts, jewelry, key chains, toggles, or pulls.  Deer horns, sheds, antlers
Description:
You will receive (10) drilled antler tines, #1 grade A, 4"-5 1/2" long, deer antler tine similar to the ones shown in the pictures (but they will be drilled!!). The pictures show an example of the stock that we pull from! All cut edges are sanded over! This is the perfect size for jewelry making, cabinet pulls, toggles & buttons and numerous other craft projects. Just let us know how many you want and we will get them right out to you! Shipping will remain the same as long as they all fit in the standard flat rate box; so buy 10, 20 or 50!
OUR STORY:
We decided to start making dog chews and antler craft items after years of collecting deer and elk antlers here in Northwest Montana. All antlers are natural shed antlers,meaning that they fall off every spring and regrow through the summer. My family and I spend numerous hours searching the woods for these allusive sheds. We (myself, my wife and our three children (2 girls and one boy) love the outdoors and decided this would be a great way to reuse these sheds. All funds from the sell of these chews will go towards their college fund!! As parents, this is a way that we can help our children appreciate the outdoors and hopefully create a passion that will last a lifetime!! Thanks again for your consideration of our products. Take a look at our other listing as our inventory will change weekly.
* 100% Natural ANTLER - No Additives. 
* Will not clog up your chewing dog's digestive system like ropes, rubber, bark, rocks. 
* No Colors to stain your carpet 
* No chemicals like plastic chews, heavy starches or artificial flavors. 
* Full of natural minerals 
* No Splintering, Long Lasting- Great for Dogs that love to chew. 
* Come from Wild Deer and Elk as they naturally shed their antlers once a year. 
* All antlers are Cut and Sanded to prevent sharp points. 
* Also good for your small pets that need to gnaw on items to keep their teeth from overgrowing!! 
Or place near your squirrel feeder and watch the critters find them.
Antler Grading:
**** We try our best to describe the grade of each of our antlers. This is particularly important to determine the correct sizing for your dog. Our grades are as follows:
#1 Grade A antlers - Brown to Light brown / white with no visible cracking or other surface defects - Longer lasting and greater life chew; perfect for an aggressive chewer or puppy! 
#2 Grade A antlers - White with visible hairline cracking - Great for elderly dogs or dogs that get bored easily; horn slightly softer and easier to break down. 
#3 Grade antlers - White chalky - not suitable for chews! 
Disclaimer:
* All chews have the potential to be a choking hazard. As with any chew, supervision is always advised. If your pet has any issues with these chews or any other chew, take away and discard immediately. 
* Antler chews and other hard chews have been known to cause tooth fractures. If your pet is elderly or has sensitive teeth, we suggest using the #2 grade antler (these are slightly softer due to laying in the sun longer). 
* Once the chew has become small from excessive chewing, discard remaining chew to reduce risk of choking. This is true of all chews (whether rawhide, plastic or antler). 
Shipping: 
We ship out every day! These will all be shipped out with flat rate boxes / envelopes from our local USPS store. We try our best to ship these as quickly as we can and pass along the actual shipping cost (unlike others that reduce the price of their chews, but increase the price of their shipping). We are happy to combine shipping, so please wait to make final payment until we send out your final invoice.

Description:
This listing is for a DIGITAL PATTERN only featuring the stained glass panel named in the title of this listing. This pattern is intended for intermediate glass artisans. There are 81 pieces in this pattern. The final project measures 19.5 X 10.5 inches before framing.
WHAT YOU GET: When you download this pattern, you will receive at least 3 files. Two will be pattern files in “PDF” format ready to print. One file will print on standard letter size paper and is for reference. The other will be a full size to scale pattern. You will also receive a colour “JPG” format file of the finished stained glass project.  
HOW TO GET THE PATTERN: The pattern will be available as an instant downloadable PDF as soon as your payment has been processed. Look for the link on your purchase receipt. A link will also be sent to your Etsy e-mail address within moments following your purchase.
You can also find the downloads in our Etsy Purchases section. There will be a link called, “Files Ready to Download” next to your order/transaction information.
This purchase is non-refundable. You are buying a digital pattern – not a finished product or kit. These are electronic PDF and JPG files that you have to print out yourself. 
You will need to print 2 full sized patterns; one to use as a master for fitting and the other to cut apart and trace onto your glass choices. I am generally providing the design only but some patterns have additional detail. If the pattern is not already numbered, you will need to number each piece correspondingly on both patterns. If grain lines are not on the pattern, I would also recommend that you draw these lines on the individual pieces prior to cutting so that all glass runs in the same direction according to the design. For example, distant hills or trees should be vertical and sky and water pieces should be horizontal.
PATTERN DISCLAIMER: Please note that the pattern files and finished project photo file may differ slightly. I have chosen to modify most patterns after production of the finished project  for the following reasons: either to make it easier, enhance the design or reduce the number of required pieces. Changes are minor in nature though and should not prevent  you from using the photo as your guide in glass and colour selection.
This pattern is for PERSONAL USE ONLY; it may not be sold. I hold copyrights to all my patterns. However, you may sell finished projects that you create from my patterns.
©Copyright by Fire Light Glass Art
WHAT YOU NEED: You will require a PDF reader program to view and use PDF files. I recommend ADOBE ACROBAT READER. This small program may be downloaded from ADOBE.COM. You can also search online for “download Adobe Acrobat Reader”. You may also use this link (accurate as of Jan 2017): http://get.adobe.com/reader

The Nature of Art Glass: Unlike common window glass, which is perfectly smooth and flawless, art glass seeks visual character through aesthetic "imperfections." These characteristics mimic the hand-made sheet glass of centuries past. They come in the form of textural waves and striations, random seeds (air bubbles) and a variety of other natural effects. Art glass achieves its personality through these peculiarities, and no two sheets are ever identical.

Avoid exposing your jewelry to perfumes and household chemicals such as when cleaning with bleach or ammonia (or when swimming in chlorinated water) as these chemicals can permanently damage gold filled jewelry. To clean your gold filled jewelry, simply use dish soap and hot water or a jewelry polishing cloth.
Gold Filled Rings:  Exposure to lotions, high humidity levels, and individual body chemistry can sometimes cause gold rings to leave your finger temporarily green. This is not a defect and can even happen with solid gold rings. The discoloration typically is harmless and washes right off with soap and water. To prevent your ring from turning your finger green, take care to keep perfumes, lotions (especially Victoria's Secret!) and other chemicals away.
