Product name: Vintage 1920/1930s Miriam Haskell Style Carved Mother of Pearl Shell  Faux Pearl Silk Cord Necklace
Description:
This vintage late 1920s/early 1930s necklace features carved Mother of Pearl shell and faux pearls sewn on  silk cord with a mother of pearl button at the end.  The necklace is not marked, but is similar in style to early Miriam Haskell jewelry.  It measures approximately 14 1/4" in length by 18" in width.  
According to Cathy Gordon & Sheila Pamfiloff's book, Miriam Haskell Jewelry, 2004, specifically with regard to identifying early pieces, "Some of the earliest necklaces and bracelets, circa the late 1920s-early 1930s, had the beads, leaves and other decorative elements mounted on silk cord, either as a single strand or sewn together to create a wider underlying structure.  The cord was sewn into a loop, and a bead, pearl, shell, or element continuing the design theme completed the jewelry closure by being passed through the loop.  In other instances, the cords were left long, sometimes with decorative elements on the ends, and the wearer tied the cords at the desired length."  
The silk cord is dirty and the mother of pearl button is loose.  This piece is in great condition and is a wonderful treasure to add to any collection.
Thank you for viewing my offerings!

The Process:
Electroforming is the process of slowly building a layer of metal on a non conductive surface using electroplating techniques. An object is painted with an conductive paint, placed in an electroforming solution and then hooked up to an electrical rectifier. Slowly a layer of metal builds up. It can take between 12-32 hours.
Taken from Rio Grande's website:
The Health Benefits of Copper
Modern science confirms what people around the world have known for hundreds of years. Copper is an essential nutrient, playing a vital role in keeping bones, skin, brain, blood vessels and immune system strong and healthy. Copper also has anti-bacterial properties useful in slowing the spread of illnesses. Because copper can be absorbed through the skin, wearing copper jewelry has become a simple, popular way to reap the benefits of this lovely metal. Although modern science has not provided specific evidence of the health benefits of copper jewelry, many still swear by it, and copper jewelry remains in high demand.

excerpt from the Vintage Fashion Guild....
Alix of Miami was one of the many manufacturing businesses that sprang up in Miami, Florida in the mid 20th century. In the post-World War II period, the city of Miami, Florida became a leader in the development of “modern” mid 20th Century design. The city’s location lent itself to modernism with a twist of tropical.
Alix of Miami made beautiful cocktail and dinner dresses with a tropical edge. They also made glamorous swimsuits, which were often studded with rhinestones.
Not much is known about the company. Two of the important figures in the business were Alix Schneidman and Luther V. Powell, who later worked at Serbin, another Miami clothing manufacturer. We believe the company was open from the early 1950s into the 1960s.
Written by Lizzie Bramlett, fuzzylizzie.com

Product name: Felt grey winter boots Felted woolen shoes Boho snow valenki Wool painting bullfinch titmouse Felt birds Warm soft footwear Rubber sole
Description:
Felt shoes Women winter boots Valenki Snow woolen boots Needle felting Felted bird Wool painting
These felted boots (unisex) or valenki* are made of natural sheep’s wool. I use only organic products and stuffs in my work: pure organic wool, warm water and soap. The process of felting the shoes continue over two weeks. At first, I felt many layer of wool till they are hard and tight. That is why the woolen shoes perfectly keep their shape but also let your feet skin breathe.
Valenki are perfect in light snow and harsh frost. They accumulate the warmth particularly in the area of sole.
The rubber soles are made of thermoelastolayer. That is why the foots don’t slide and don’t rip during the frost. The soles are water-resistant. Your feet won't get cold even in minus 30 C degrees.
The felted wool is a thermal and breathable material, maintaining the perfect temperature any time of year. Felt is a perfect material for footwear. It is extremely wear proof and warm. When you put them on, you won't want to take the shoes off, because they are cozy, soft and comfortable inside. They will definitely make a part of your winter outfit.
These shoes are decorated with the prettiest winter birds – bullfinch and titmouse. For creating the birds, I used barbed needle, multicolor merino wool and my phantasy. This technique called needle felting or wool painting: a barbed needle felt together wool fibers onto a flat wool felt surface.
♥ We promise you a warm pleasure with my felt footwear.
♥ Ask us for other color, design, painting or size! Natalia would like to make something individual for you to order.
♥ Please keep in mind any colors may look different in real life due to your screen settings.
♥ Check out other felt outdoor shoes and boots:

________________
*(Wikipedia):
"Valenki are traditional Russian winter footwear, essentially felt boots: the name valenok literally means "made by felting". Valenki are made of wool felt. Valenki were once the footwear of choice for many Russians, but in the second half of the 20th century they lost most of their appeal in cities, due to their association with rustic dress. Valenki are a kind of traditional Russian footwear which is usually worn for walking on dry snow when the weather is frosty".

Product name: My Lucky Shrooming Bag For Mushroom Hunters. Tough tear resistant scuba mesh, solid bottom
Description:
I am an avid Morel Mushroom Hunter.   I can honestly say that - this bag is the most comfortable & practical mushroom hunting bag on the market!
   This is a 15 x 17 inch mushroom hunting bag made out of tough tear resistant mesh used by scuba divers around sharp reefs.   It has a thick very comfortable adjustable strap that you can adjust into a handle or over the shoulder bag.  We also added the solid bottom to protect the morels or any other wild mushrooms from crushing as the bag gets filled.  The mesh we use is thicker with smaller holes which also protects your mushrooms from grating, while still spreads the spores as you walk through the woods. 
   
   It is proudly made in the USA.   I have been working with this company for a while to perfect them, just got them in right at the peak of my mushroom hunting season.  Took a few bags for a test run..   I am very very happy with how they turned out!     I was even lucky enough to fill it up under 2 elm trees.
  Another awesome feature about this bag is I wore it over my head & shoulder .. as I was picking morels,  the bag was right in front of my chest to put the mushrooms in, which freed up both of my hands for picking.  And as I moved through the woods at a decent speed the bag hangs just a bit higher which allows me to move fast without smacking the bag around with my legs with precious morel mushrooms.
  The bag comes with a 8 inch pocket that reads "My Lucky Shrooming Bag".  You can fold the bag & the strap into the pocket for off season storage.
 We are very proud of this design, hope you enjoy it as well.
 The mesh is needed when you pick morel mushrooms to release the spores so they plant else where, start a new mycelium growth & will keep producing mushrooms in the same as well as new areas.  Using a mesh bag also keeps your mushrooms fresh.  Plastic bags suffocates the mushrooms where they start the spoiling process and onion/ grapefruit bags are not designed for delicate spongy morel mushrooms so they end up grating the morels.
   The mesh is very sturdy.  We use high quality mesh material so you don't have to  worry about ripping your mushroom bag with precious morel mushrooms in it.
 I run through the woods from spot to spot due to season being so short & don't want to worry about  ripping one of these bags when they snag on the lims.  
    Unique and thoughtful gift.
   We are in love with mushroom hunting & look forward to spring every year to harvest the elusive morel mushrooms.  We travel from state to state picking them to prolong our season, covering up to 12 states.
  Morel Mushrooms Etsy Shop has been born out of pure desire and dedication to giving our fellow mushroom hunters & nature lovers products to show off and wear proudly!   We are a very small, family owned outdoor gear company and would greatly appreciate you telling your nature loving friends and family about us.
  If you haven't yet, please check out the rest of our Morel Mushrooms Etsy Shop with our other unique Morel Mushroom & Nature loving products.  Also like our Mushroom Gear page on Facebook
Thank you for visiting Morel Mushrooms Shop and Happy Shrooming!  
      May your skillet stay full this spring!   :)

Product name: Brown Leather Bag // Large Leather Tote // Soft Leather Bag
Description:
Perfect everyday leather tote in a beautiful distressed saddle brown color.
This leather tote was inspired by my father-in-law's leatherwork from the 70s, which often featured a mix of complimentary earthtone browns and contrast topstitching.  The design is simple, yet elegant, to showcase the beauty of the raw materials.  The tote is soft, casual, and unstructured.  
// Approximate Dimensions //
 - 13" high x 16.5" wide x 4" deep
 - 9" Strap Drop
 - Slip Pocket = 8" wide x 6.5" high
 - Unlined
 - Full grain leather**
 - Saddle-grade Vegetable Tanned Straps
 - Solid Brass Key Ring
*Need an Extra Pocket on the other side? No problem:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/462828316/
*Need a structured, flat bottom for your bag? Add this option:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/479063919/
The tote features beautifully distressed, Italian full-grain, full-aniline saddle brown leather**.  This leather is sort of like your favorite pair of worn-in jeans - perfectly imperfect, with color and texture variations throughout.  The full-grain leather may or may not have healed scars, scratches, etc.  The straps are made of saddle-grade American vegetable tanned bridle leather and are strong, yet supple, and cured with waxes to help them stand up to the elements. The straps are top stitched for strength and beauty, as well as burnished for comfort and to seal the leather. The tote is unlined and has one interior slip pocket for your phone and keys. 
**Leather is a natural material, and I only use full grain leather, which is authentic and is considered the finest grade, as it has not been sanded down and resurfaced during the tanning process. This means that the leather may have natural markings, wrinkles, scars, small blemishes, etc., which are considered "signature" of fine leather, and become part of the rustic, distressed texture of this bag.  Every hide comes from a unique cow, and as such, there may be variations in color and texture both within a bag and between bags, and no two totes will be exactly alike - leaving you with a bag that is uniquely yours!
More Colors Available!

Product name: Hand stitched leather belt
Description:
Bespoke leather belt made on demand.
I stitch my belts by hand using the traditional saddler's stitch. The tools (Blanchard) and the linen thread ("Fil au Chinois") I use are the very same than those used by the famous leathercrafters on the market.
 
This belt is made of 3 layers of full grain vegetable tanned leather. The middle layer gives this raised effect. This model is 1 1/4 inch (32 mm) wide, thickness is 4 mm on the edges and 6 mm between the lines of stitches which are made of a single thread on each side. Several colours combinations are possible for inside/outside layers and thread colour.

Jersey or denim turbans
 As this product is hand finished a gentle hand wash in warm water is safest. Then dry flat. As the knots are made of thick material and take a while to dry you can just wash the band for a quick clean.
Velvet turbans
